WEBVTT

00:36.002 --> 00:38.237
[♪♪♪]

00:38.371 --> 00:40.206
[CROWD CHEERING]

00:43.910 --> 00:46.679
[BASKETBALL BOUNCING]

00:50.950 --> 00:53.386
ANNOUNCER 1:
The entire season is hanging
in the balance here.

00:53.519 --> 00:55.922
ANNOUNCER 2:
It's Beck to the rack
with another dunk!

00:56.055 --> 00:57.523
That's his second straight.

00:57.657 --> 00:58.858
ANNOUNCER 1:
Senior Scott Beck,

00:58.991 --> 01:00.393
with seconds on the clock...

01:00.526 --> 01:01.728
ANNOUNCER 2:
Six straight points for Beck.

01:01.861 --> 01:03.262
ANNOUNCER 1:
He shoots from deep.

01:03.396 --> 01:04.697
ANNOUNCER 2:
Here comes Beck.

01:04.831 --> 01:06.131
ANNOUNCER 1:
And it's a goal!

01:06.265 --> 01:07.467
Texas Christian wins!

01:07.600 --> 01:09.135
ANNOUNCER 2:
Beck on the dribble,

01:09.268 --> 01:10.970
Beck scores!

01:09.268 --> 01:10.970
ANNOUNCER 1: Are you kidding?

01:11.104 --> 01:12.906
ANNOUNCER 2:
Beck scores again!

01:13.039 --> 01:15.775
ANNOUNCER 1:
That's the most incredible shot
I've ever seen.

01:15.908 --> 01:19.245
ANNOUNCER 2:
On the D. Another
last-minute save by Scott Beck.

01:19.378 --> 01:20.780
ANNOUNCER 1:
Unbelievable performance

01:20.914 --> 01:22.582
by Scott Beck.

01:20.914 --> 01:22.582
ANNOUNCER 2: Amazing!

01:22.715 --> 01:26.219
Scott Beck coming in 30 points
a game, an all-American.

01:26.352 --> 01:29.355
What wouldn't you want
in Scott Beck?

01:37.363 --> 01:40.500
Good morning, Knoxville.
And the phones are lighting up.

01:42.201 --> 01:44.170
We're remembering
Knoxville Prep greats

01:44.304 --> 01:48.274
but ones who could never
quite make it to the big dance.

01:50.543 --> 01:52.845
REPORTER 1:
The real upset this year
is Scott Beck.

01:52.978 --> 01:56.182
REPORTER 2:
It's hard not to look at
Scott Beck as a disappointment.

01:56.315 --> 01:58.484
REPORTER 1:
Completely overlooked
in the NBA draft.

01:58.618 --> 02:00.620
MAN 1:
Remember that outside shot
he used to have?

02:00.753 --> 02:03.122
REPORTER 2:
It's really a shame
to see someone like that.

02:03.256 --> 02:05.258
A complete disappointment.

02:03.256 --> 02:05.258
REPORTER 1: Heartbreaking.

02:05.391 --> 02:07.693
But more common than not.
What a shame.

02:07.827 --> 02:09.229
MAN 2:
Really a shame.

02:11.464 --> 02:13.533
MAN 3:
Obviously, he didn't have
what it takes

02:13.666 --> 02:15.635
to be a star in the NBA.

02:21.941 --> 02:24.844
[GENE BUTLER'S "A BEGGAR
FOR YOUR LOVE" PLAYING]

02:28.981 --> 02:32.451
♪ I need a handout, baby ♪

02:32.585 --> 02:34.487
♪ I'm starvin' for love ♪

02:36.956 --> 02:40.459
♪ I need a handout, baby ♪

02:40.593 --> 02:42.662
♪ I'm starvin' for love ♪

02:44.931 --> 02:48.034
♪ I need a handout, baby ♪

02:48.167 --> 02:51.171
♪ I'll be a beggar
For your love ♪

02:53.106 --> 02:55.875
♪ Well, when I come knockin' ♪

02:56.008 --> 02:58.544
♪ In my worn-out shoes ♪

02:58.678 --> 03:00.713
[DOG BARKING]

03:00.847 --> 03:03.950
♪ Yeah, when I come knockin' ♪

03:04.083 --> 03:06.085
♪ In my worn-out shoes... ♪

03:07.286 --> 03:08.688
[SIGHS]

03:10.689 --> 03:12.258
So you're the culprit.

03:14.059 --> 03:15.027
What do you want?

03:15.161 --> 03:16.095
[BARKS]

03:16.229 --> 03:18.498
Shoo. Go away.

03:19.832 --> 03:20.833
Shoo.

03:20.966 --> 03:22.535
[WHINING]

03:24.604 --> 03:26.972
REPORTER [ON TV]:
And now for
the "Knoxville Minute."

03:27.106 --> 03:29.075
The traffic this morning
is actually pretty light

03:29.208 --> 03:30.576
heading into
downtown Knoxville.

03:30.709 --> 03:32.178
The heat wave, as we expected,

03:32.311 --> 03:34.314
arrived late last night,
so it's going to be

03:34.447 --> 03:35.748
a bit of a scorcher
out there today

03:35.881 --> 03:37.583
and pretty much
in all of Knox County.

03:37.717 --> 03:39.419
Hope those air conditioners
are doing their job.

03:39.552 --> 03:40.853
And as for you, our viewers,

03:40.986 --> 03:42.355
I hope you have a great day.

03:43.756 --> 03:45.758
[PHONE RINGING]

03:48.894 --> 03:49.996
Hello?

03:52.197 --> 03:54.734
Well, when was his appointment?

03:54.867 --> 03:57.237
I'm... I'm not sure
why he didn't show up.

03:57.370 --> 04:00.239
Sometimes my dad forgets things.

03:57.370 --> 04:00.239
[KNOCKS ON DOOR]

04:00.372 --> 04:03.910
Uh, I'm gonna have
to call you back and reschedule.

04:06.245 --> 04:08.281
Oh, yeah. I'll make sure
he shows up this time.

04:10.449 --> 04:12.752
Hi, Mrs. Walcott.

04:10.449 --> 04:12.752
Your rent's due.

04:12.885 --> 04:14.954
I know. I'm... I'm sorry.

04:15.088 --> 04:16.622
And you need to feed this dog

04:16.756 --> 04:18.590
before it wakes
the whole neighborhood.

04:18.724 --> 04:21.261
The thing is, it's not my dog.

04:21.394 --> 04:25.531
Well, she thinks she's your dog.
What's her name?

04:25.665 --> 04:28.467
I don't know.
I think her tag says Lucky.

04:28.600 --> 04:30.603
This dog look lucky to you?

04:36.376 --> 04:39.145
It's Lucy. Her name is Lucy.

04:39.278 --> 04:42.849
Okay. Um, well, um...
Have a great day.

04:43.916 --> 04:44.984
Thank you.

04:45.117 --> 04:47.619
Oh, and another thing.

04:45.117 --> 04:47.619
Yep.

04:47.753 --> 04:50.256
There's a lot of holes
in my yard.

04:50.390 --> 04:52.091
Now, I don't know
who's digging them,

04:52.224 --> 04:53.692
whether it's Lucy or you...

04:53.825 --> 04:58.331
but it needs to stop.

04:53.825 --> 04:58.331
Absolutely. I'll look into it.

04:58.464 --> 05:00.800
[♪♪♪]

05:06.805 --> 05:09.108
REPORTER:
Look, no one's questioning
Ryan Aikens' right

05:09.242 --> 05:11.277
to cut Dobbs and Monroe.
I mean, that's what happens

05:11.410 --> 05:13.879
when your daddy leaves you
a professional basketball team.

05:14.012 --> 05:16.516
But who are we kidding?
I'm questioning the logic.

05:16.649 --> 05:18.750
I mean, come on!
With their star players gone

05:18.884 --> 05:20.786
and less than a month
before the season starts,

05:20.920 --> 05:24.290
the Knights' roster
looks more like an obituary.

05:24.423 --> 05:27.426
Hi, Ruby. Are they here yet?

05:24.423 --> 05:27.426
Half are.

05:27.560 --> 05:29.696
I can bet which half is not.

05:33.132 --> 05:35.668
Banks will be here soon.

05:35.802 --> 05:37.936
We both know
he's not showing up, Archie.

05:38.070 --> 05:41.306
You got to remember,
he's an old-school coach.

05:41.440 --> 05:44.076
Cutting Dobbs and Monroe,
two best guys on the team,

05:44.209 --> 05:45.411
without consulting--

05:45.545 --> 05:47.112
Dobbs and Monroe are
both criminals.

05:47.246 --> 05:48.848
We all know that.
Domestic violence,

05:48.981 --> 05:50.148
allegations of point shaving...

05:50.282 --> 05:52.051
Excuse me, I did not say
I'd miss them.

05:52.184 --> 05:55.287
I'm just saying that
it's embarrassing to a coach

05:55.420 --> 05:57.856
to cut his two best players
without consulting him.

05:57.990 --> 06:00.826
Not to mention,
the general manager.

06:00.959 --> 06:02.328
What do you think of Okoye?

06:02.462 --> 06:03.996
In the practice sessions
he's been doing--

06:04.130 --> 06:06.132
[PHONE RINGS]

06:06.265 --> 06:08.000
Coach's office.

06:06.265 --> 06:08.000
I called a meeting,

06:08.133 --> 06:10.903
and where are you?

06:08.133 --> 06:10.903
Where I always am, Ms. Aikens,

06:11.036 --> 06:13.239
where the real work of
managing this team takes place.

06:13.372 --> 06:16.576
Not that ivory tower of yours.
Your father understood that.

06:16.709 --> 06:19.244
Every day that Dobbs and Monroe
stayed on that roster,

06:19.378 --> 06:21.013
they shamed my father's team.

06:21.146 --> 06:23.115
They scored points.

06:21.146 --> 06:23.115
They scored ratings.

06:23.249 --> 06:24.717
My father was old-school.

06:24.850 --> 06:27.186
He coddled his players
and ignored the accountants.

06:27.319 --> 06:29.855
I need players. There's a few
I've got my eye on.

06:29.989 --> 06:32.858
Well, I have my eye
on a stack of pending lawsuits,

06:32.992 --> 06:36.428
IRS notices,
past-due vendor invoices.

06:36.562 --> 06:39.465
[SIGHS]
The truth is,
we barely have the money

06:39.598 --> 06:42.001
to pay the players
that we have now,

06:42.134 --> 06:44.570
and the board is threatening
to move the franchise.

06:46.072 --> 06:47.706
So you tried to put out a fire

06:47.839 --> 06:49.075
by throwing gasoline on it.

06:49.208 --> 06:51.110
Maybe it's time
I took up fishing.

06:51.243 --> 06:52.945
No, no, no. Hear me out.

06:53.079 --> 06:56.548
I may have a solution to this
and it's a bit unconventional,

06:56.682 --> 06:59.786
but why don't we try
open tryouts?

06:59.919 --> 07:02.154
We'd look desperate.

06:59.919 --> 07:02.154
We'll look like clowns.

07:02.287 --> 07:04.423
It's an event.
It's unique and promotable.

07:04.556 --> 07:06.225
We could do
a three-round process

07:06.358 --> 07:08.127
where the fans
are engaging in drama

07:08.260 --> 07:09.928
and they have underdogs
to root for.

07:10.062 --> 07:12.932
Are we rebuilding a franchise
or casting a reality show?

07:13.065 --> 07:17.803
Reality show that airs
every night on SportsCenter

07:17.936 --> 07:21.807
and all day on social media
and in the press.

07:21.941 --> 07:24.944
There could be some talent
out there, coach. We don't know.

07:25.077 --> 07:26.912
Your father would turn over
in his grave

07:27.045 --> 07:28.280
if he knew what you were doing.

07:28.414 --> 07:30.315
Now, if you'll excuse me,

07:30.449 --> 07:32.618
I have a team to coach.

07:32.751 --> 07:33.986
Baker.

07:36.755 --> 07:38.024
He'll come around.

07:38.157 --> 07:41.527
As long as he has final say
on the players.

07:41.660 --> 07:42.995
You all right?

07:45.097 --> 07:47.667
My father trusted me
with his team, Archie.

07:50.569 --> 07:53.439
Your father had
two great sayings.

07:54.607 --> 07:56.275
One of them, I won't say now,

07:56.408 --> 07:57.509
but the other one is:

07:57.643 --> 07:59.745
"Don't be afraid of losing,

07:59.878 --> 08:03.015
because winning
doesn't teach you anything."

08:03.148 --> 08:06.018
And remember, it's not
your father's team anymore.

08:06.152 --> 08:07.520
It's yours.

08:26.572 --> 08:28.708
[ENGINE SPUTTERING]

08:32.445 --> 08:36.081
$300 for new tires.
$450 brake job.

08:36.215 --> 08:39.185
I have to go to work now,
but when I get back...

08:39.318 --> 08:41.354
I expect a better attitude.

08:43.889 --> 08:46.993
WOMAN [OVER PA]:
Attention, all students.
It's that time of year again.

08:47.126 --> 08:49.661
Friday will be the official day
to clean out all lockers.

08:49.795 --> 08:51.897
Anyone interested in trying
out for the soccer team,

08:52.031 --> 08:53.766
please be on
the south field today...

08:53.899 --> 08:57.802
Scott, I forgot
my locker combination again.

08:57.936 --> 08:59.705
Okay, Darcey. I'll get to it.

08:59.838 --> 09:02.841
Oh, and are you the one
that fixes the air conditioners?

09:02.975 --> 09:04.977
Uh, yeah, I just fixed
the one in chem lab.

09:05.110 --> 09:07.045
Which one's broken now?

09:05.110 --> 09:07.045
The one in chem lab.

09:07.179 --> 09:08.948
[SCHOOL BELL RINGS]

09:07.179 --> 09:08.948
Hey, Scott.

09:10.482 --> 09:12.017
How you doing, my friend?

09:10.482 --> 09:12.017
[SIGHS]

09:12.150 --> 09:14.086
Car just died
in the parking lot.

09:14.220 --> 09:18.591
You know, when God closes
a door, he opens a window.

09:18.724 --> 09:20.359
You okay, Nick?

09:20.492 --> 09:22.561
Yeah, I'm just practicing
my "pastor speak."

09:22.694 --> 09:25.230
I really think I'm gonna
give seminary another shot,

09:25.364 --> 09:28.067
so I'm back
in anger management classes.

09:28.200 --> 09:30.402
How many times have you
flunked seminary school?

09:30.536 --> 09:32.871
Three.
Okay. Four, all right?

09:33.004 --> 09:34.907
But that last one did not count.
It was online.

09:35.040 --> 09:37.042
It's not like
they expelled me. They just...

09:37.176 --> 09:39.044
removed my user ID
and password.

09:39.178 --> 09:40.746
All right, just calm down.

09:40.879 --> 09:42.180
How can I help?

09:42.314 --> 09:44.283
Actually, if you would
do me a favor

09:44.416 --> 09:46.752
and hang these FCA fliers up
in the cafeteria?

09:46.885 --> 09:49.454
I'm gonna have
my first meeting tomorrow.

09:49.588 --> 09:50.956
Sure.

09:49.588 --> 09:50.956
Thanks, man.

09:51.089 --> 09:52.291
Yeah.

09:51.089 --> 09:52.291
Oh.

09:52.424 --> 09:53.959
Are you gonna
come to practice tonight?

09:54.092 --> 09:55.327
Uh, depends on when I get done.

09:55.460 --> 09:57.029
Listen, I'm gonna
tell these guys

09:57.163 --> 09:58.864
that they have to pay you
to help me coach.

09:58.997 --> 10:01.133
This volunteer thing
has been going on for too long.

10:01.266 --> 10:03.602
Yeah. I'll get there
as soon as I can.

10:03.735 --> 10:05.437
All right.

10:05.571 --> 10:07.940
Don't forget to hang them up.

10:05.571 --> 10:07.940
Okay.

10:10.443 --> 10:11.344
[SIGHS]

10:16.415 --> 10:17.816
HAL [ON RECORDING]:
Leave a message.

10:17.949 --> 10:19.084
[LINE BEEPS]

10:19.217 --> 10:21.153
Hey, Pop. It's me.

10:21.286 --> 10:23.389
I haven't heard from you
in a little while.

10:23.522 --> 10:25.758
Wanna make sure you're okay.

10:25.891 --> 10:29.095
The doc called. Anyway, just...

10:30.529 --> 10:32.164
Just call me back, okay?

10:33.298 --> 10:34.433
Miss you.

10:35.501 --> 10:36.602
[BEEPS]

10:38.103 --> 10:41.007
[♪♪♪]

10:43.175 --> 10:44.944
[CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING]

10:46.478 --> 10:48.347
Thank you all for coming.

10:49.447 --> 10:50.315
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

10:50.449 --> 10:51.583
This weekend,

10:51.716 --> 10:53.618
the Knoxville Silver Knights

10:53.752 --> 10:57.322
will be holding
open tryouts at the arena.

10:57.456 --> 11:00.425
We're hoping to put
some of that American dream

11:00.559 --> 11:03.262
back into
this all-American team.

11:12.037 --> 11:14.740
There you go, Darcey.
Another day, another lock.

11:25.250 --> 11:26.985
NICK:
Come on, Cooper!

11:27.119 --> 11:28.920
Man, Grandma was slow,
but she was old.

11:29.054 --> 11:31.022
Let's go.
We have a game tomorrow.

11:31.156 --> 11:32.724
Hustle, guys!

11:32.858 --> 11:34.393
Hey. Sorry I'm late.

11:34.526 --> 11:36.862
Somebody got sick
in the cafeteria.

11:36.995 --> 11:39.531
What's with the beef jerky?

11:39.665 --> 11:41.801
It's part
of my anger management courses.

11:41.934 --> 11:44.003
Supposedly, it keeps me
from blowing a gasket

11:44.136 --> 11:46.172
whenever I get riled up.
Come on!

11:46.305 --> 11:47.806
You're gonna get fouled,
Johnson!

11:47.940 --> 11:49.075
Don't step on the line!

11:50.208 --> 11:51.177
So did you hear?

11:52.477 --> 11:53.512
What?

11:55.214 --> 11:56.348
[LAUGHS]

11:59.585 --> 12:00.886
It's Ryan.

12:01.020 --> 12:03.088
At her impromptu
press conference today,

12:03.222 --> 12:05.257
Ryan Aikens,
Silver Knights' team owner,

12:05.391 --> 12:08.226
announced the team's plan
to hold open tryouts

12:08.360 --> 12:10.062
for local residents.

12:08.360 --> 12:10.062
Unbelievable.

12:10.196 --> 12:12.998
I know, right?
She still looks good.

12:13.131 --> 12:17.235
No. I mean, yeah.
But open tryouts?

12:17.369 --> 12:19.504
Murphy! Under the basket!

12:19.637 --> 12:21.373
Let's go. Come on.

12:21.506 --> 12:22.775
What do you think?

12:22.908 --> 12:25.578
I haven't spoken to Ryan
in almost 20 years.

12:25.711 --> 12:27.779
We didn't exactly end things
on the right foot.

12:27.913 --> 12:30.415
Just say you're sorry
and go to the tryouts.

12:30.549 --> 12:33.786
I'm pretty sure an "I'm sorry"
is past its expiration date.

12:33.919 --> 12:36.822
Look, man, you were so close
to getting to the NBA.

12:36.956 --> 12:39.625
Everybody knows
you got robbed.

12:39.758 --> 12:43.062
That was almost 20 years ago.
Those days are behind me.

12:43.195 --> 12:44.930
And what about the days
in front of you?

12:46.898 --> 12:48.567
My father stopped
seeing his doctor,

12:48.700 --> 12:51.937
my sink leaks, and my car needs
a new electrical system.

12:52.071 --> 12:53.805
My plate's pretty full
right now.

12:53.939 --> 12:56.107
That doesn't sound full.

12:56.241 --> 12:57.776
Kind of sounds
a little pathetic.

12:57.909 --> 12:59.077
Hold this.

12:59.211 --> 13:01.079
All right, Murphy,
for the last time,

13:01.213 --> 13:03.115
do I have to bring your mom
to teach you the difference

13:03.248 --> 13:05.283
between left and right?

13:03.248 --> 13:05.283
No, sir.

13:05.417 --> 13:06.752
[NICK CLAPS]

13:09.555 --> 13:11.457
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

13:19.731 --> 13:21.267
[TRANSMISSION SPUTTERS, CLICKS]

13:25.170 --> 13:27.173
[TRANSMISSION CLICKING]

13:29.107 --> 13:31.644
[GENE BUTLER'S
"GONE BABY BLUES" PLAYING]

13:33.179 --> 13:36.615
♪ In the middle of the night ♪

13:36.749 --> 13:40.285
♪ When the cold sweat comes ♪

13:40.419 --> 13:43.589
♪ And there's a beating
In your chest ♪

13:43.722 --> 13:47.193
♪ That firing squadron ♪

13:49.261 --> 13:53.665
♪ When the problems
On your mind ♪

13:53.799 --> 13:55.500
♪ Ain't a deadly kind ♪

13:55.634 --> 13:57.068
[SIGHS]

13:57.202 --> 13:59.538
♪ And you feel stuck
On a ladder ♪

13:59.671 --> 14:01.807
♪ With no climb ♪

14:03.609 --> 14:08.480
♪ So you reach for memories ♪

14:08.614 --> 14:12.417
♪ Reach for the booze... ♪

14:12.551 --> 14:14.286
REPORTER:
...new owner of the Knights,
Ryan Aikens,

14:14.419 --> 14:17.656
wasted no time
on her surprising announcement.

14:17.789 --> 14:19.324
She's taking a huge risk

14:19.458 --> 14:22.561
and bringing her team
much-needed attention.

14:25.697 --> 14:27.499
Hey.

14:27.632 --> 14:28.834
Okay.

14:28.967 --> 14:30.502
Next time you feel like barking,

14:30.636 --> 14:32.137
you chew on that, all right?

14:34.205 --> 14:35.774
Okay. Come on inside.

14:35.907 --> 14:37.276
Come on. Come on.

14:37.409 --> 14:38.644
Okay.

14:41.346 --> 14:44.516
♪ Those gone baby blues ♪

14:46.718 --> 14:52.091
♪ Those gone baby blues ♪

14:53.792 --> 14:55.694
...local team's ambitious owner

14:55.827 --> 14:57.562
certainly has
a lot on her plate.

14:57.696 --> 15:00.198
Let's take a closer look
at the press conference.

15:00.332 --> 15:03.235
We're hoping to put
some of that American dream

15:03.369 --> 15:06.237
back into
this all-American team.

15:06.371 --> 15:07.972
[RECORDING REWINDS]

15:08.106 --> 15:10.842
We're hoping to put
some of that American dream

15:10.976 --> 15:14.079
back into
this all-American team.

15:14.212 --> 15:16.548
...into this all-American team.

15:18.883 --> 15:20.285
...American team.

15:20.418 --> 15:23.455
[♪♪♪]

15:28.393 --> 15:29.561
[WHINES]

15:50.849 --> 15:52.750
You need to go home
and get some rest.

15:52.884 --> 15:55.420
Your daddy would tell you
there will be plenty of time

15:55.554 --> 15:58.122
for you to second-guess
yourself tomorrow.

15:58.256 --> 15:59.591
Aw, thank you, Ruby.

15:59.724 --> 16:01.994
Good night.

15:59.724 --> 16:01.994
Good night, honey.

16:11.069 --> 16:12.270
MURPHY: Scott.

16:11.069 --> 16:12.270
Murph.

16:12.404 --> 16:14.806
Wow, you're here early.

16:14.939 --> 16:17.809
Uh, you think you can give my
car a jump after school today?

16:17.943 --> 16:19.511
When are you gonna get
a new car?

16:19.645 --> 16:22.114
Uh, when I get new money.

16:19.645 --> 16:22.114
[CHUCKLES]

16:23.615 --> 16:26.151
What? Something on your mind?

16:26.284 --> 16:28.787
I just wanna know
what I'm doing wrong out there.

16:28.920 --> 16:32.156
Are you nervous
about the Clayton game tonight?

16:32.290 --> 16:34.293
Nothing. You're gonna do fine.

16:34.426 --> 16:38.530
Come on, man. Everybody knows
that's you in the trophy case.

16:38.663 --> 16:40.131
You're the man.

16:40.265 --> 16:41.633
Come on, give me some advice.

16:41.766 --> 16:43.835
Yeah. You're too young
to be stressing.

16:43.969 --> 16:45.671
Just have fun.

16:47.439 --> 16:49.174
I just wanna play in the NBA.

16:50.675 --> 16:51.777
You do, huh?

16:53.311 --> 16:55.314
All right, well, just, you know,

16:55.447 --> 16:57.549
don't put all your eggs
in one basket.

16:57.683 --> 16:58.784
Have options.

17:00.319 --> 17:02.420
Yeah, well, coach says
our dreams

17:02.554 --> 17:05.724
are God's way of telling us what
we should do with our lives.

17:05.857 --> 17:08.027
Coach told you that?

17:10.695 --> 17:12.397
All right. Uh...

17:12.530 --> 17:14.932
Yeah. You know what?

17:15.066 --> 17:16.868
That's me in the trophy case.

17:17.001 --> 17:18.637
I was a Lion once.

17:18.770 --> 17:22.641
And this is me now.

17:22.774 --> 17:24.809
You know what I'm saying?

17:24.943 --> 17:26.245
Yeah.

17:26.378 --> 17:28.514
Best advice I can give you,
buddy.

17:35.520 --> 17:38.424
[♪♪♪]

17:57.242 --> 18:00.311
NICK:
Welcome to the FCA.

18:00.445 --> 18:02.047
[SIGHS]

18:02.180 --> 18:05.016
We are the Fellowship
of Christian Athletes.

18:05.149 --> 18:09.721
Um, but you don't have to be
either to come check us out.

18:11.556 --> 18:13.158
We're made of a bunch of people

18:13.291 --> 18:15.594
from a bunch
of different places.

18:18.063 --> 18:20.299
Yeah. No one showed up.

18:20.432 --> 18:22.701
I didn't think it was
a good enough reason to cancel,

18:22.834 --> 18:24.569
you know, so...

18:24.702 --> 18:27.239
And what would have been
a good enough reason?

18:27.372 --> 18:30.475
Don't get smart with me, man.

18:27.372 --> 18:30.475
All right.

18:30.608 --> 18:34.112
Truth is, I kind of needed
the practice anyway, so...

18:34.245 --> 18:37.716
All right, well, practice on me.

18:37.849 --> 18:39.084
For real?

18:39.217 --> 18:40.819
Sure.

18:40.953 --> 18:42.787
Okay. Um...

18:42.921 --> 18:45.156
Well, we can start
from the discussion.

18:45.289 --> 18:48.293
In John 10:10...

18:48.427 --> 18:52.797
"The thief comes only to steal
and kill and destroy.

18:52.930 --> 18:56.635
But I have come so that
you may have abundant life."

18:58.270 --> 18:59.371
What?

19:02.073 --> 19:04.009
Nothing. Go on.

19:05.910 --> 19:06.979
All right.

19:08.780 --> 19:10.082
Spit it out, man.

19:11.216 --> 19:12.984
I don't know. I mean,

19:13.118 --> 19:15.820
I'm just thinking about
the whole abundant-life thing.

19:15.954 --> 19:19.824
Is that really the promise
that you wanna make these kids?

19:19.958 --> 19:22.494
It's not my promise.
It's God's.

19:22.627 --> 19:24.362
I mean, you see

19:24.496 --> 19:26.998
very many abundant lives
around here, Nick?

19:27.132 --> 19:29.001
Because from where
I'm sitting...

19:30.602 --> 19:33.205
I just see a lot of regret
and hopelessness.

19:35.640 --> 19:37.209
And who's gonna
pick up the pieces

19:37.342 --> 19:39.111
when things go south
for these kids?

19:39.244 --> 19:41.046
You?

19:41.179 --> 19:43.514
God? Jesus?

19:43.648 --> 19:46.718
You know, you can't blame God
for your choices, Scott.

19:46.851 --> 19:48.353
That's on you.

19:49.554 --> 19:51.923
Look, I'm sorry. Okay?

19:52.056 --> 19:54.792
I haven't been
in a very good mood these last--

19:54.926 --> 19:56.328
Fifteen years.

20:00.632 --> 20:01.766
All right, you know what?

20:01.900 --> 20:03.701
I think you got it
under control.

20:03.835 --> 20:05.037
I'll see you later.

20:07.205 --> 20:09.208
[CROWD YELLING INDISTINCTLY
AND SHOES SQUEAKING]

20:18.216 --> 20:19.685
[BUZZER SOUNDS]

20:25.223 --> 20:27.693
NICK:
We're getting
our heads kicked in out there!

20:29.394 --> 20:31.330
And I don't see any heart.

20:33.497 --> 20:34.967
From none of you!

20:41.373 --> 20:44.209
You know what? Coach Scott
might have something to add.

20:46.244 --> 20:47.613
[DOOR SLAMS]

20:51.850 --> 20:55.921
Look, Coach Martin's working
through some stuff, okay?

20:57.388 --> 20:59.757
So, yeah, just, uh, you know...

20:59.891 --> 21:03.829
go out there
and have some fun with it.

21:05.630 --> 21:08.100
You can't take this all
so seriously.

21:10.201 --> 21:11.803
It's just a game.

21:13.671 --> 21:14.906
Go on.

21:27.585 --> 21:29.121
Wait.

21:33.625 --> 21:34.760
Come here.

21:43.868 --> 21:44.770
All right.

21:45.904 --> 21:47.673
You guys do have heart.

21:49.074 --> 21:50.808
But to win...

21:50.942 --> 21:53.545
you gotta use your heads.

21:53.678 --> 21:55.613
You have to be smart.

21:55.746 --> 21:57.682
You have to think.

21:57.815 --> 22:00.952
Average height
of a Clayton player is what?

22:01.085 --> 22:02.320
They're big, coach.

22:02.454 --> 22:04.155
Yeah, they're bigger than us,
right?

22:04.288 --> 22:06.725
Half their points
are off rebounds.

22:06.858 --> 22:10.328
So every time a shot goes up,
what do you do?

22:10.462 --> 22:13.798
You find your man
and you box him out.

22:13.931 --> 22:15.834
Every time.

22:18.569 --> 22:20.939
For if we control the boards...

22:22.640 --> 22:24.476
then this game is ours.

22:25.810 --> 22:26.878
Bring it in.

22:27.979 --> 22:29.281
Murph, on three.

22:29.414 --> 22:31.316
"Lions" on three.
One, two, three.

22:31.449 --> 22:32.383
ALL:
Lions!

22:32.517 --> 22:34.019
[PLAYERS EXCLAIMING]

22:36.888 --> 22:39.991
[♪♪♪]

22:46.831 --> 22:47.966
[BUZZER SOUNDS]

22:48.099 --> 22:50.035
[CROWD CHEERING]

23:04.148 --> 23:06.050
NICK:
Proud of you guys. You did it.

23:06.184 --> 23:09.186
Each and every one of you.
Now, come on, let's head out.

23:09.320 --> 23:11.957
I'll catch up with you in a sec.

23:09.320 --> 23:11.957
Hey. Good game, Coop.

23:13.358 --> 23:14.526
Thank you.

23:17.829 --> 23:19.331
Thank you.

23:19.464 --> 23:21.733
I'm happy to help out.

23:21.866 --> 23:24.035
We're gonna go eat some pizza.
You wanna come?

23:24.169 --> 23:26.271
I gotta finish up here.

23:24.169 --> 23:26.271
Well, hurry it up

23:26.404 --> 23:29.373
and keep thinking about
those tryouts.

23:29.507 --> 23:33.077
I know you still want it.

23:29.507 --> 23:33.077
What are you talking about?

23:33.211 --> 23:34.612
Come on.

23:34.746 --> 23:36.414
Everybody knows it.

23:36.547 --> 23:37.916
Word gets around.

23:38.049 --> 23:39.818
Are you spying on me?

23:39.951 --> 23:41.319
Look, I'm just saying.

23:41.452 --> 23:43.588
Why is this so important to you?

23:43.721 --> 23:46.624
How's anyone gonna
let me pastor a church

23:46.757 --> 23:49.795
if I can't convince you that God
wants you to live a full life?

23:50.929 --> 23:52.197
So I'm a test case.

23:53.431 --> 23:55.066
No, man.

23:55.199 --> 23:56.835
You're my best friend.

23:59.704 --> 24:00.972
[CHUCKLES]

24:01.105 --> 24:03.375
♪ Right or wrong ♪

24:05.210 --> 24:07.645
♪ Who's to blame? ♪

24:07.779 --> 24:09.280
[PHONE RINGS]

24:09.413 --> 24:10.749
♪ It's all the same... ♪

24:10.882 --> 24:12.350
Hello.

24:12.483 --> 24:14.019
Wait, he's doing what?

24:15.453 --> 24:17.655
Okay, Bernie.
I'll be right over.

24:17.789 --> 24:18.990
Thanks.

24:20.891 --> 24:23.094
HAL:
I paid for it! I can hear it!

24:23.227 --> 24:25.830
All right. Seven times
in one night's plenty.

24:25.963 --> 24:28.800
What do you know about it?

24:25.963 --> 24:28.800
Take him, Scott.

24:28.933 --> 24:31.703
Scottie!

24:28.933 --> 24:31.703
I know, Pop. Come on.

24:33.805 --> 24:35.073
Let's get you home, Pop.

24:35.206 --> 24:37.142
I love you.

24:39.377 --> 24:40.278
Hey, Pop.

24:41.813 --> 24:43.448
Why are you making such a fuss

24:43.582 --> 24:45.717
over a song on the jukebox?

24:47.118 --> 24:49.754
And why aren't you going
to your doctor?

24:51.756 --> 24:52.958
What's going on?

24:54.659 --> 24:56.494
Insurance stopped paying.

24:56.628 --> 25:00.866
So unless you wanna drive me
to Canada twice a month...

25:05.470 --> 25:08.206
They said I need a new heart.

25:10.174 --> 25:11.943
I don't want a new heart.

25:13.211 --> 25:14.746
What would I do with it?

25:14.879 --> 25:16.881
REPORTER [ON TV]:
The arena is getting prepared

25:17.015 --> 25:19.083
for what looks like
a fun and exciting moment

25:19.216 --> 25:22.453
in the league's
first-ever open tryouts.

25:22.587 --> 25:24.789
And more importantly,
the community is ready

25:24.922 --> 25:27.292
for the first look
at who will show up

25:27.425 --> 25:28.926
for this exciting opportunity.

25:29.060 --> 25:30.327
Look at her.

25:30.461 --> 25:31.762
She thinks she's somebody,

25:31.896 --> 25:34.065
now that her old man died.

25:34.198 --> 25:37.001
Ryan's okay.

25:34.198 --> 25:37.001
She quit on you,

25:37.135 --> 25:40.004
the minute she saw you weren't
gonna amount to nothing.

25:40.138 --> 25:42.874
That's not what happened, Pop.

25:40.138 --> 25:42.874
A woman like that

25:43.007 --> 25:45.844
doesn't marry a janitor,
Scottie.

25:49.046 --> 25:51.082
Yeah, I guess you're right.

25:51.215 --> 25:55.019
It don't make a lick
of difference now, anyhow.

25:55.153 --> 25:56.555
What's done...

25:57.789 --> 25:59.190
is done.

26:01.759 --> 26:03.762
It was that Elvis song.

26:04.895 --> 26:06.131
The one she liked.

26:11.802 --> 26:13.071
Needed to...

26:15.506 --> 26:16.641
hear it.

26:36.227 --> 26:38.430
[♪♪♪]

26:44.869 --> 26:46.471
MURPHY:
"Lions" on three.
One, two, three.

26:46.604 --> 26:47.739
ALL:
Lions!

26:47.872 --> 26:49.674
[PLAYERS EXCLAIMING, CLAPPING]

26:56.080 --> 26:58.816
Hello, Knights fans.
Today, hundreds of hopefuls wait

26:58.950 --> 27:00.752
for their shot
in owner Ryan Aikens'

27:00.885 --> 27:03.989
much publicized
and criticized open tryouts.

27:08.159 --> 27:10.061
Go ahead and follow
that group to the gym

27:10.195 --> 27:11.396
and run through the drills.

27:11.529 --> 27:12.997
They'll let you know
if you come back.

27:13.130 --> 27:15.967
Thanks.
Uh, why the practice gym?

27:16.101 --> 27:18.169
Coach said nobody plays
on the official court

27:18.302 --> 27:19.971
until they've earned the right.

27:20.104 --> 27:21.306
Good luck.

27:27.445 --> 27:30.348
[♪♪♪]

27:57.141 --> 27:58.309
Lord...

27:59.678 --> 28:02.947
I know
I can't talk to my father.

28:03.081 --> 28:04.415
[SIGHS]

28:04.549 --> 28:06.484
So I was really hoping that...

28:07.952 --> 28:09.888
maybe you could ask him...

28:11.356 --> 28:14.825
what I'm supposed to do,
because I'm not...

28:14.959 --> 28:17.629
I'm not sure
about anything anymore.

28:19.664 --> 28:22.199
And if that doesn't work,
then...

28:22.333 --> 28:25.603
I was really hoping
that you could give me a clue.

28:27.405 --> 28:29.374
[BASKETBALL BOUNCING]

28:37.715 --> 28:41.719
Hey, excuse me.
Tryouts are in the practice gym.

28:41.853 --> 28:44.689
I know, I-- I just was--

28:47.024 --> 28:48.726
Scott?

28:48.860 --> 28:50.328
Is that you?

28:52.563 --> 28:53.732
Hey, Ry.

28:57.534 --> 28:59.336
Wait, are--?

28:59.470 --> 29:01.772
Are you trying out?

29:01.905 --> 29:04.575
Aren't you, like, 40?

29:04.709 --> 29:06.744
Not yet.

29:06.878 --> 29:08.612
My birthday isn't
until November 17th.

29:08.746 --> 29:10.215
November 17th.

29:19.190 --> 29:20.458
How you been?

29:21.559 --> 29:22.660
Real busy.

29:24.395 --> 29:25.997
Of course, and...

29:27.732 --> 29:29.167
I'm sorry about your dad.

29:30.868 --> 29:31.903
Thank you.

29:33.671 --> 29:34.739
You look good.

29:35.940 --> 29:38.275
I mean, you look well.

29:38.409 --> 29:40.111
I mean, you know-- And...

29:41.278 --> 29:42.280
Good.

29:42.413 --> 29:44.182
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

29:44.315 --> 29:47.051
Ms. Aikens,
Archie's looking for you.

29:47.184 --> 29:48.386
I have to go.

29:49.921 --> 29:51.155
Hey, Ry.

29:51.289 --> 29:53.357
Are you really
so surprised to see me?

29:53.491 --> 29:55.293
I mean, you must
at least thought

29:55.426 --> 29:57.162
there was a chance I'd show up.

29:58.329 --> 30:00.498
Why would I think of you at all?

30:02.967 --> 30:05.904
[♪♪♪]

30:17.548 --> 30:20.851
ARCHIE:
Isn't that Scott Beck
over there?

30:20.985 --> 30:22.186
RYAN:
Mm-hm.

30:22.319 --> 30:25.789
Pretty good luck.

30:22.319 --> 30:25.789
Forget it, Archie.

30:25.923 --> 30:29.961
I'm not gonna trot out some
old romance for the cameras.

30:30.094 --> 30:31.895
Couldn't hurt, though.

30:32.029 --> 30:33.631
It hurt the first time.

30:44.942 --> 30:46.477
What are you doing?

30:46.610 --> 30:48.813
Engaging the fans.

30:48.947 --> 30:51.216
Giving them some drama
to follow.

30:52.516 --> 30:53.852
[BLOWS]

30:56.353 --> 30:58.723
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

30:58.856 --> 31:01.759
[♪♪♪]

32:04.889 --> 32:06.757
REPORTER [ON TV]:
Well, the story begins

32:06.891 --> 32:10.060
for this exciting
yet risky move by Ms. Aikens.

32:10.194 --> 32:12.063
Her father, a legend,

32:12.196 --> 32:15.132
now passes on his legacy
to his ambitious daughter.

32:15.265 --> 32:17.668
We do know
she has what it takes.

32:17.801 --> 32:19.637
The million-dollar question is,

32:19.771 --> 32:23.641
will someone show up
and bring what she needs?

32:23.774 --> 32:26.778
Did you see Ryan?

32:23.774 --> 32:26.778
She's kind of hard to miss.

32:28.946 --> 32:30.080
And?

32:30.214 --> 32:32.583
And I don't want
to get my hopes up.

32:32.717 --> 32:34.084
Why not?

32:34.218 --> 32:36.453
I mean, it's better to see
the glass half-empty.

32:36.587 --> 32:38.756
So when it spills,
you're not a wreck.

32:38.889 --> 32:40.425
Oh, right. Okay.

32:40.558 --> 32:45.129
So our God, all powerful,
fountain of all wisdom.

32:45.262 --> 32:46.831
You've got to play it safe,
right?

32:46.964 --> 32:48.833
The abundant-life thing again.

32:46.964 --> 32:48.833
[STAMMERS]

32:48.966 --> 32:51.969
Forget about that. Let's go
with your half-empty thing.

32:52.103 --> 32:54.138
Jesus came so he could
take that glass,

32:54.271 --> 32:57.107
half-empty, full,
broken, whatever.

32:57.241 --> 32:59.610
He came
so that he could refill it.

33:01.112 --> 33:03.314
I'm pretty sure Ryan hates me.

33:06.917 --> 33:08.686
Okay, we can work through that.

33:10.454 --> 33:13.457
Oh, come on.
Atlanta will never let him go.

33:13.591 --> 33:14.959
Make a deal with Atlanta.

33:15.092 --> 33:18.161
We don't have the money.
What about the tryouts?

33:18.295 --> 33:19.730
How about Darryl Coates?

33:19.864 --> 33:23.935
His score is 23.2 per game,
6.7 on rebounds.

33:24.068 --> 33:25.369
ARCHIE:
Wait, where'd he play?

33:25.503 --> 33:28.272
Iraq, Qatar and Afghanistan.

33:28.405 --> 33:30.374
ARCHIE: A war hero.

33:28.405 --> 33:30.374
Are we making headlines

33:30.508 --> 33:32.476
or rebuilding this team?

33:30.508 --> 33:32.476
[SIGHS]

33:32.609 --> 33:34.378
Hopefully both.

33:34.512 --> 33:36.748
This might be
an interesting option for you.

33:40.117 --> 33:41.519
This should be good.

33:48.626 --> 33:49.994
[DOG BARKING]

33:50.127 --> 33:52.563
♪ When you think
That it's over ♪

33:54.298 --> 33:56.968
♪ When you think
That you're done ♪

33:58.603 --> 34:02.673
♪ When you're ready
To give up... ♪

34:02.806 --> 34:04.275
Lucy.

34:04.408 --> 34:06.043
[WHISTLES]

34:06.176 --> 34:07.445
Come here.

34:07.578 --> 34:10.882
Look, all I have is
some pizza crust, okay?

34:11.015 --> 34:11.916
All right.

34:15.886 --> 34:17.822
[ENGINE SPUTTERING]

34:26.697 --> 34:30.768
♪ Little piece of the sun ♪

34:30.902 --> 34:35.673
♪ Little piece
Of the sun ♪

34:35.806 --> 34:39.944
♪ Reach up and touch ♪

34:40.078 --> 34:43.414
♪ A little piece of the sun ♪

34:46.684 --> 34:51.088
♪ When you're stuck
On the bottom ♪

34:51.222 --> 34:53.958
♪ And the world weighs a ton ♪

34:55.760 --> 35:00.565
♪ When all hope is empty ♪

35:00.698 --> 35:03.100
♪ And you're facing
The gun... ♪

35:03.233 --> 35:04.635
[PANTING]

35:04.768 --> 35:06.737
Where have you been?

35:06.871 --> 35:09.306
My car and I aren't speaking
right now.

35:09.440 --> 35:12.576
Hey, uh, don't argue
with Pastor Lawrence.

35:12.710 --> 35:15.079
I need God on my side today.
Thanks.

35:15.212 --> 35:17.148
Actually, I was...

35:17.281 --> 35:18.382
saving that for you.

35:18.515 --> 35:20.784
Yeah. Okay. Sure.

35:20.918 --> 35:23.687
Before we begin,
I have a special prayer request

35:23.821 --> 35:25.690
for our very own Scott Beck.

35:27.090 --> 35:29.259
Scott, we are rooting

35:29.393 --> 35:30.761
and praying for you.

35:37.734 --> 35:41.471
Proverbs 3:6 tells us:

35:41.605 --> 35:43.274
"In all your ways,

35:43.407 --> 35:45.475
submit to him...

35:45.609 --> 35:48.145
and he will
make your paths straight."

35:48.279 --> 35:51.248
Not all translations
say it that way.

35:51.382 --> 35:54.118
If you humble yourselves
before the Lord...

35:56.020 --> 35:59.356
all the answers
to life's questions...

35:59.490 --> 36:02.960
are easy to find.

35:59.490 --> 36:02.960
Except Proverbs 25:2 says

36:03.093 --> 36:05.530
it's the glory of God
to conceal a thing, so...

36:07.798 --> 36:09.366
A lot of times
we go through life

36:09.500 --> 36:11.001
and we go through challenges
and we--

36:11.135 --> 36:14.772
We want to just stop and quit.

36:14.905 --> 36:20.545
What if the Lord would have quit
up on that cross?

36:26.484 --> 36:27.584
SCOTT:
Thanks, pastor.

36:27.718 --> 36:29.853
That was a great service.

36:27.718 --> 36:29.853
Thank you.

36:29.987 --> 36:32.055
So how you think
it went yesterday?

36:32.189 --> 36:35.392
I don't know. I'm supposed
to find out tomorrow.

36:35.526 --> 36:37.261
I coach a little basketball
myself.

36:37.394 --> 36:40.131
Oh, yeah? Like a church league?

36:37.394 --> 36:40.131
Not exactly.

36:40.264 --> 36:42.533
We're at the rec center
most weekends.

36:42.666 --> 36:44.568
Come down, the guys
would love to meet you.

36:44.702 --> 36:46.503
Yeah. Um...

36:44.702 --> 36:46.503
[PHONE BUZZING]

36:46.637 --> 36:49.240
I'm sorry, pastor. Excuse me.

36:49.373 --> 36:52.643
Hello?

36:49.373 --> 36:52.643
Pastor Lawrence.

36:52.776 --> 36:54.611
Love that passion, heh-heh.

36:54.745 --> 36:56.280
Yeah, I'm gonna
have to challenge you

36:56.413 --> 36:58.249
on that Proverbs 3:6
"straight line" thing.

36:58.382 --> 37:01.084
Hey, why don't you come by
the office during the week?

37:01.218 --> 37:02.386
We'll talk about it.

37:05.656 --> 37:08.226
That was Ryan.
She's on her way to my place.

37:09.426 --> 37:11.162
Do you want me to take you?

37:11.295 --> 37:12.196
Let's go.

37:17.501 --> 37:22.105
NICK:
I'm not saying he's a heretic.
I'm just saying he's not right.

37:22.239 --> 37:25.242
Pastor Lawrence is old-school.
I'm what's happening now.

37:25.376 --> 37:27.378
Besides, I get my guidance
from the Lord.

37:27.511 --> 37:28.980
He's got me
exactly where he wants.

37:30.180 --> 37:31.582
SCOTT:
Oh, she's here.

37:31.715 --> 37:33.216
NICK:
Ooh.

37:33.350 --> 37:36.987
You sure you don't want me
to go in there with you?

37:37.121 --> 37:39.123
Um, I think I can handle it.

37:41.491 --> 37:43.261
Was that Nick Martin?

37:44.929 --> 37:47.565
Yeah, he's still around.

37:51.868 --> 37:54.038
You, uh... You want to come in?

37:55.439 --> 37:57.274
Since when did you get a dog?

37:57.407 --> 37:58.909
It's not my dog.

38:01.645 --> 38:03.080
You want some tea?

38:12.389 --> 38:15.993
Well, I'm not gonna pretend
that this isn't weird.

38:18.429 --> 38:20.931
So, what's going on, Ryan?

38:21.065 --> 38:23.634
Well, I came to tell you

38:23.767 --> 38:26.070
that Coach Banks
is releasing a list of players

38:26.203 --> 38:29.439
who've made it
to the second round and...

38:29.573 --> 38:30.541
you're on that list.

38:32.743 --> 38:35.313
You just have
to sign your life away.

38:38.014 --> 38:41.519
Is everyone on that list getting
a visit from the team's owner?

38:44.722 --> 38:46.991
Just the ones
that she almost married.

38:49.927 --> 38:52.762
Uh, look, I know that I, um--

38:52.896 --> 38:54.498
Why are you doing this, Scott?

38:54.631 --> 38:58.635
Why are you putting yourself
through this again?

38:58.768 --> 38:59.704
Both of us.

39:01.939 --> 39:04.675
Well, it's not like
I couldn't use the money.

39:04.808 --> 39:06.577
There's easier ways
to make a buck

39:06.710 --> 39:09.213
than trying to play
professional basketball at 40.

39:09.346 --> 39:12.483
Thirty-nine. And maybe
I'm not going for easy.

39:12.616 --> 39:14.651
Look around. It's not
like I got a lot to lose.

39:14.785 --> 39:16.820
Well, I do.
You asked me if I thought

39:16.954 --> 39:18.722
you were gonna show up
at the tryouts,

39:18.855 --> 39:21.392
but did you ask yourself
what I might think or feel

39:21.525 --> 39:23.226
if you actually did?

39:23.360 --> 39:26.296
If I knew it was gonna upset
you, I wouldn't have come down.

39:26.430 --> 39:28.065
What did you expect, Scott?

39:29.466 --> 39:31.201
You basically left me
at the altar

39:31.335 --> 39:33.270
and then you just disappeared.

39:33.404 --> 39:37.007
I tried to call you, but
they said you were in Europe.

39:37.140 --> 39:40.243
That was after I hadn't
seen you in, like, a year.

39:40.377 --> 39:42.412
Look, I, uh...

39:42.546 --> 39:45.216
Things didn't go the way
that I had expected.

39:45.349 --> 39:46.684
Obviously.

39:46.817 --> 39:47.884
The draft.

39:48.018 --> 39:50.387
Yeah, I know.

39:50.521 --> 39:53.557
But it's not my fault
that you didn't have a plan B.

39:54.692 --> 39:56.660
How do you know this isn't it?

39:58.729 --> 40:00.530
Look, I just came by
to tell you

40:00.664 --> 40:03.434
that Banks is putting you
through to the second round,

40:03.567 --> 40:06.370
and you're gonna get a lot
of attention from the press.

40:06.503 --> 40:09.606
That's what a big part
of this is.

40:09.739 --> 40:12.075
And you're gonna bet
that they're gonna ask

40:12.209 --> 40:14.578
a lot of questions about us.

40:16.713 --> 40:18.215
Two sugars, right?

40:21.718 --> 40:25.388
I appreciate you coming by
and warning me.

40:25.522 --> 40:27.958
I can't promise you anything.

40:28.091 --> 40:29.360
Of course.

40:31.695 --> 40:36.133
What's that saying about life's
unexpected twists and turns

40:36.266 --> 40:38.235
and fate and all that?

40:38.369 --> 40:39.670
I don't know. I'll ask Nick.

40:39.804 --> 40:41.672
He's pretty good
with all that stuff.

40:41.805 --> 40:43.807
Is he still trying
to become a preacher?

40:43.941 --> 40:45.476
Yeah. The guy won't quit.

40:47.277 --> 40:50.447
Hey, what makes you think
that you can make it now

40:50.581 --> 40:52.216
when you couldn't
in your prime?

40:53.717 --> 40:55.586
Maybe I gave up too soon.

41:07.831 --> 41:09.533
Your dog needs a bath.

41:11.234 --> 41:12.837
It's not my dog.

41:15.005 --> 41:17.007
Good to see you, Jerry.

41:17.140 --> 41:22.679
♪ You bring me back to you ♪

41:22.812 --> 41:25.516
♪ Ooh-ooh ♪

41:25.649 --> 41:28.085
♪ Ooh-ooh ♪

41:28.218 --> 41:33.257
♪ Ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh
Back to you ♪

41:35.426 --> 41:37.728
You want me to cut through
and then pass it to Cooper,

41:37.861 --> 41:40.230
or cut through and then go--?

41:37.861 --> 41:40.230
Come on, guys!

41:40.364 --> 41:42.132
I'm gonna have
to get you on roller skates.

41:42.265 --> 41:45.135
That's what I'll have to do.
You know what? Get out there.

41:45.269 --> 41:46.470
Come on.

41:50.507 --> 41:52.609
You got me on pins and needles.
What happened?

41:52.743 --> 41:54.477
[WHISPERS INDISTINCTLY]

41:54.611 --> 41:57.047
You got it? Yeah, you--

41:57.180 --> 42:00.216
Yeah! Hey, guys!
Scott's a Silver Knight!

42:00.350 --> 42:03.187
[ALL CHEERING]

42:06.356 --> 42:09.260
[♪♪♪]

43:16.193 --> 43:18.829
SCOTT:
Cooper on the wing.
He's not available.

43:18.962 --> 43:21.064
Murphy, you're underneath.
All right?

43:21.197 --> 43:24.368
Look, guys, we haven't beaten
Broadmoor in 30 years,

43:24.501 --> 43:26.937
but they have their weaknesses,

43:27.070 --> 43:29.706
and we have
the home-court advantage.

43:29.840 --> 43:32.409
Guys. Put your phones down.

43:35.712 --> 43:37.580
You used to be
with the Knights' owner?

43:37.714 --> 43:39.115
We're not playing the Knights.

43:39.249 --> 43:42.353
She's hot.

43:39.249 --> 43:42.353
Yeah. No.

43:43.487 --> 43:44.455
Come on.

43:45.555 --> 43:46.490
[SIGHS]

43:46.623 --> 43:49.026
All that is just hype.

43:49.159 --> 43:52.329
It doesn't mean anything.

43:49.159 --> 43:52.329
MURPHY: It kind of does.

43:54.331 --> 43:56.232
You just went from the guy
in the trophy case

43:56.366 --> 43:58.068
to the guy in the Knox Arena.

43:59.636 --> 44:01.605
I don't know. It's like maybe--

44:01.738 --> 44:04.441
I mean, we can do it too, right?

44:04.574 --> 44:05.676
Right?

44:07.144 --> 44:08.646
Right, Scott Beck?

44:13.650 --> 44:16.120
All right. See you tomorrow.

44:20.090 --> 44:21.625
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

44:23.593 --> 44:26.664
I mean, Scott--
Scott was amazing.

44:26.797 --> 44:29.099
I mean, he was one of the best.
You hear me?

44:31.467 --> 44:34.137
You know
what Scott's quality was?

44:34.270 --> 44:37.440
He would make everything
look easy.

44:37.574 --> 44:40.344
Everyone was in shock
that they never selected him.

44:41.778 --> 44:44.682
[♪♪♪]

44:51.121 --> 44:53.757
We know that in victory
or defeat,

44:53.891 --> 44:56.393
your will and your plan
are perfect.

44:56.526 --> 44:58.661
And we ask--

44:58.795 --> 45:02.465
And we ask for patience,

45:02.599 --> 45:05.368
for safety, for courage
and humility.

45:05.502 --> 45:06.903
In Jesus' name, we pray.

45:07.037 --> 45:08.371
Amen.

45:07.037 --> 45:08.371
ALL: Amen.

45:08.504 --> 45:10.674
All right, guys. Good job.

45:08.504 --> 45:10.674
Sorry to interrupt.

45:14.311 --> 45:19.082
Uh, Kristina Walsh, Channel 6.
I--

45:19.216 --> 45:21.951
I am the coach of the Lions.
Nick Martin.

45:22.085 --> 45:24.454
But you're probably looking
for this guy.

45:24.587 --> 45:25.922
Scott Beck.

45:26.056 --> 45:27.091
Yeah...

45:30.727 --> 45:32.496
Yeah. Uh, seriously? No.

45:32.629 --> 45:35.432
No, thanks.

45:32.629 --> 45:35.432
Scott. Please.

45:35.566 --> 45:39.603
The whole town wants to know
what's going on. Five minutes.

45:39.736 --> 45:41.672
Um...

45:44.174 --> 45:45.242
[SIGHS]

45:47.077 --> 45:49.079
Okay.

45:49.212 --> 45:51.582
KRISTINA:
Considering your past
romantic involvement

45:51.715 --> 45:54.584
with Ryan Aikens, do you think
she can effectively do her job

45:54.718 --> 45:55.985
as the Knights owner?

45:56.119 --> 45:57.921
SCOTT:
Let me tell you about Ryan.

45:58.054 --> 46:00.424
After high school,
a lot of people were surprised

46:00.557 --> 46:03.060
when she went against
her Ivy League dad's wishes

46:03.193 --> 46:05.228
and enrolled
in Texas Christian.

46:05.361 --> 46:07.363
She never used
her family's money

46:07.497 --> 46:09.232
or influence for anything.

46:09.366 --> 46:11.034
And, yeah,
cutting Dobbs and Monroe,

46:11.168 --> 46:12.569
that was a hard choice,

46:12.702 --> 46:15.939
but it was a choice
towards integrity.

46:16.073 --> 46:17.941
And, yeah,
I fell in love with Ryan.

46:18.074 --> 46:20.643
And so will this city
when they see what she can do.

46:20.777 --> 46:23.679
The Knights are in good hands.

46:20.777 --> 46:23.679
Beck is joined by...

46:23.813 --> 46:26.582
The U.S. Daily Observer
and Champion Illustrated

46:26.716 --> 46:28.918
are running stories
on their sites tomorrow, so...

46:29.052 --> 46:31.288
Yeah, well, it may be
a little too soon to tell,

46:31.421 --> 46:34.457
but I think that we might
just turn this around.

46:34.591 --> 46:38.762
Never underestimate the power of
a really good Cinderella story.

46:38.895 --> 46:42.098
Best not to leave them
feeling foolish for believing.

46:42.231 --> 46:44.334
If you're worried about
Scott Beck, don't be.

46:44.468 --> 46:48.371
Next round's a real punisher,
and he's no college kid.

46:48.505 --> 46:52.142
He's gonna drop out before it's
a problem for either one of us.

46:54.110 --> 46:55.879
[PHONE RINGING]

46:54.110 --> 46:55.879
KRISTINA: Thanks for joining.

46:56.013 --> 46:58.381
I am Kristina Walsh with
the Channel 6 weather team.

46:58.514 --> 47:00.116
HAL [ON RECORDING]:
Leave a message.

47:00.250 --> 47:02.152
[ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS]

47:02.285 --> 47:05.355
SCOTT:
Hey, Pop, I'm on television
if you wanna watch.

47:05.489 --> 47:06.857
Channel 8.

47:09.259 --> 47:11.294
I made it
to the second round, Pop.

47:11.428 --> 47:12.663
Call me.

47:19.369 --> 47:24.340
♪ Through you
I can do anything ♪

47:24.474 --> 47:27.577
♪ I can do all things ♪

47:27.710 --> 47:30.747
♪ Because it's you
Who gives me strength ♪

47:30.881 --> 47:34.051
♪ Nothing is impossible ♪

47:46.663 --> 47:50.901
♪ I'm not gonna live
By what I see ♪

47:53.703 --> 47:58.175
♪ I'm not gonna live
By what I feel ♪

48:00.177 --> 48:05.849
♪ Deep down I know
That you're here with me ♪

48:05.982 --> 48:12.255
♪ I know that
You can do anything ♪

48:12.389 --> 48:13.857
[WHINES]

48:13.990 --> 48:17.727
♪ Through you
I can do anything ♪

48:17.861 --> 48:20.596
♪ I can do all things ♪

48:20.730 --> 48:24.400
♪ 'Cause it's you
Who gives me strength ♪

48:24.534 --> 48:26.603
♪ Nothing is impossible ♪

48:26.736 --> 48:30.873
♪ Through you
Blind eyes are open ♪

48:31.007 --> 48:33.810
♪ Strongholds are broken ♪

48:33.943 --> 48:35.445
♪ I am living by faith ♪

48:35.579 --> 48:37.680
Extra beef jerky for us today.

48:37.814 --> 48:41.084
♪ Nothing is impossible ♪

48:41.217 --> 48:43.887
REPORTER:
It's Day 2 for
the Silver Knights open tryout.

48:44.020 --> 48:45.888
Already, we're seeing
standouts,

48:46.022 --> 48:49.359
like local high-school
star athlete Scott Beck

48:49.493 --> 48:52.663
making a name for himself again
with his outside shot.

48:55.532 --> 48:56.466
Hey, man.

48:56.600 --> 48:58.768
Coates. Yeah? I'm Scott.

48:58.901 --> 49:00.470
Hey, I just wanna say thank you.

49:00.603 --> 49:02.139
During the sprint,
making it into a race,

49:02.272 --> 49:04.674
the whole competition effect.

49:02.272 --> 49:04.674
A competition?

49:04.808 --> 49:06.442
I look at you
as a potential teammate.

49:06.576 --> 49:09.312
Well, either way, if you hadn't,
I wouldn't be here today.

49:09.445 --> 49:10.647
Yeah.

49:10.780 --> 49:13.884
[♪♪♪]

49:19.522 --> 49:22.092
They look a lot taller
in real life.

49:38.575 --> 49:41.611
I've coached basketball
for 30 years.

49:43.580 --> 49:47.751
This is not how I saw
my final year.

49:47.884 --> 49:51.254
If I had my way, I'd send
all of you home right now.

49:51.387 --> 49:53.023
But after today,

49:53.156 --> 49:55.558
I'm gonna have to narrow it down
to three of you.

49:55.691 --> 49:58.294
For you, this is an opportunity.

49:58.428 --> 49:59.529
For me?

50:00.797 --> 50:03.132
It's an embarrassment.

50:03.266 --> 50:05.068
And I apologize for that.

50:06.803 --> 50:08.872
Since some of you will not leave

50:09.005 --> 50:12.342
until you are carried off
in a body bag,

50:12.476 --> 50:13.810
I'd like to get started now,

50:13.944 --> 50:17.380
so in the hopes
that I can accommodate you

50:17.514 --> 50:19.816
sooner rather than later.

50:19.949 --> 50:21.051
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

50:21.184 --> 50:24.121
[♪♪♪]

50:42.138 --> 50:43.040
[BLOWS]

51:28.051 --> 51:30.954
[♪♪♪]

51:54.343 --> 51:55.611
Yeah.

51:55.745 --> 51:58.582
RUSSELL:
Scott Beck, give us a word.

52:05.388 --> 52:07.524
Aren't you a little old
for this game, Beck?

52:08.624 --> 52:09.693
Aren't you?

52:10.893 --> 52:12.529
I'm a coach. I could do this

52:12.662 --> 52:14.564
till they put me in the ground.

52:14.698 --> 52:18.134
What do you got?
A couple seasons, if that?

52:18.267 --> 52:19.569
I like my odds.

52:19.702 --> 52:21.071
I've run the numbers.

52:21.204 --> 52:22.672
Your odds?

52:24.140 --> 52:25.742
I'm one of the few on the court

52:25.876 --> 52:27.444
with real competitive
game time.

52:27.577 --> 52:30.313
That leaves you
with about a dozen good options.

52:30.447 --> 52:33.549
You got two good centers,
but you only need one.

52:33.683 --> 52:37.119
And that guy Fletcher
gets 20% more rebounds

52:37.253 --> 52:38.688
than the guy
in the green shirt.

52:38.822 --> 52:41.024
But he'd have 13 fouls
in this one scrimmage.

52:41.157 --> 52:43.392
And by my count, green shirt
gets back to the goal

52:43.526 --> 52:45.595
a second quicker,
which is why I told Coates

52:45.729 --> 52:47.830
he's gotta get back faster
on defense.

52:47.964 --> 52:49.833
That's what you told him, huh?

52:56.973 --> 52:59.875
I would think after 15 years
behind a broom

53:00.009 --> 53:04.748
that you would realize this game
is about more than just numbers.

53:04.881 --> 53:08.385
Well, go on. Finish
your dance for the cameras.

53:27.270 --> 53:28.338
[SCOFFS]

53:35.712 --> 53:36.880
[SIGHS]

53:45.155 --> 53:46.523
Need a ride?

53:50.059 --> 53:51.228
Yeah.

53:55.965 --> 53:58.434
RYAN:
Why did you mouth off
to Coach Banks like that?

53:58.568 --> 54:00.570
You must have known
that humiliating him

54:00.703 --> 54:02.638
in front of everyone
probably ended

54:02.772 --> 54:06.076
whatever slim chance you had
to begin with.

54:08.377 --> 54:10.946
I'm just tired of everybody
thinking they know who I am

54:11.080 --> 54:13.149
and what I'm capable of.

54:13.283 --> 54:14.551
Fair enough.

54:15.885 --> 54:17.754
You wanna come
to the game tonight?

54:17.887 --> 54:20.089
Mm, I'm real busy.

54:20.222 --> 54:21.891
Ah.

54:22.024 --> 54:25.594
We're playing Broadmoor
at home.

54:25.728 --> 54:27.864
Even you couldn't beat
Broadmoor.

54:27.997 --> 54:30.433
Yeah, but I'm, uh...

54:30.566 --> 54:32.135
I'm smarter now.

54:34.236 --> 54:36.239
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

54:37.540 --> 54:38.475
Wait for it.

54:41.043 --> 54:42.012
Wait for it.

54:43.746 --> 54:44.948
Wait for it.

54:47.917 --> 54:49.386
Now!

54:58.194 --> 54:59.996
[BUZZER SOUNDS]

55:00.129 --> 55:02.432
[CROWD CHEERING]

55:02.565 --> 55:05.201
[♪♪♪]

55:09.072 --> 55:11.308
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

55:20.349 --> 55:21.418
Hey.

55:22.885 --> 55:24.620
You know,
I haven't been back here

55:24.753 --> 55:26.622
since I graduated.

55:26.756 --> 55:28.525
I never left.

55:28.658 --> 55:29.959
[CHUCKLES]

55:30.093 --> 55:31.761
Here's what we wanna know.

55:31.895 --> 55:34.964
A woman like you,
why would you date Scott?

55:35.098 --> 55:36.365
[LAUGHS]

55:35.098 --> 55:36.365
I mean,

55:36.499 --> 55:39.368
I'm looking at zero game here.

55:36.499 --> 55:39.368
[RYAN CHUCKLES]

55:39.502 --> 55:42.539
Well, he had it going on
back in the day.

55:42.672 --> 55:44.640
I'm a witness.

55:44.774 --> 55:47.177
I'm standing right here, guys.

55:44.774 --> 55:47.177
[ALL CHUCKLE]

55:47.310 --> 55:49.746
All right, guys, come on.
Let's get some grub.

55:53.249 --> 55:55.385
You know what?
You certainly have a lot

55:55.518 --> 55:57.720
for someone
with nothing to lose.

55:57.854 --> 56:01.191
I'm not really their coach.
That's all Nick.

56:02.658 --> 56:04.961
Yeah, but they care about you.

56:05.094 --> 56:07.130
Well, they're
a great bunch of kids.

56:15.338 --> 56:19.675
After Mom died, Dad gave up.

56:19.809 --> 56:21.611
He's just mad.

56:21.744 --> 56:23.380
Mad at everything.

56:24.680 --> 56:26.216
Fell off the wagon.

56:27.983 --> 56:30.653
Oh, man, I'm so sorry.

56:30.786 --> 56:33.189
I had no idea
you went through all that.

56:34.556 --> 56:36.759
So how did you end up

56:36.892 --> 56:38.795
back at Kings Academy?

56:42.865 --> 56:44.200
Well, it's a job.

56:45.368 --> 56:46.603
No pressure.

56:48.104 --> 56:49.439
I mean, after everything,

56:49.572 --> 56:51.540
I felt like I needed to think
for a while.

56:51.674 --> 56:53.576
[LAUGHS]

56:53.709 --> 56:56.512
Well, you know, um...

56:56.646 --> 57:00.583
15 years
is a long time to think.

57:02.751 --> 57:04.087
[WHISPERS]
I know.

57:15.631 --> 57:18.301
[♪♪♪]

57:21.904 --> 57:26.910
[SIGHS]
Well, after graduation,
I got my MBA at Oxfeld.

57:28.110 --> 57:29.779
I spent the next five years

57:29.912 --> 57:31.614
in corporate finance.

57:33.116 --> 57:34.884
I got married.

57:36.185 --> 57:37.654
I traveled the world.

57:39.088 --> 57:40.690
Oh, then I got divorced

57:40.823 --> 57:42.425
and I came back home.

57:43.959 --> 57:46.029
Daddy always told me
not to date a player.

57:46.162 --> 57:48.831
I always assumed he just meant
the kind on the court.

57:48.964 --> 57:50.767
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

57:52.735 --> 57:55.438
All right. So how did you end up
with the team?

57:55.571 --> 57:58.174
Trust me, I am as...

57:58.308 --> 58:00.777
shocked as anyone else.

58:02.245 --> 58:06.582
I think that half the city
is expecting me

58:06.715 --> 58:08.751
to fall on my face and fail,

58:08.884 --> 58:14.023
and the other half wants me to,
you know...

58:16.025 --> 58:19.395
The board wants
to move the franchise.

58:19.528 --> 58:21.731
Leave Tennessee? Why?

58:23.499 --> 58:24.801
Money.

58:24.934 --> 58:26.735
You should know,
in professional sports,

58:26.869 --> 58:28.838
it's all about the money.

58:28.971 --> 58:31.874
I'm pretty sure my father knew
that that was gonna happen,

58:32.007 --> 58:34.177
and that's why...

58:34.310 --> 58:36.613
I'm here to finish
what he couldn't.

58:39.148 --> 58:40.450
You love it?

58:43.353 --> 58:44.521
Basketball?

58:46.555 --> 58:50.159
Oh, I don't know. Ask me again
when I can actually breathe.

58:51.560 --> 58:52.896
I get it.

58:54.029 --> 58:57.433
Expectations, they wear on you.

59:00.169 --> 59:02.038
Your life, your goals...

59:04.173 --> 59:06.309
none of it belongs to you
anymore.

59:08.444 --> 59:10.647
Even your failures aren't yours.

59:14.316 --> 59:17.420
Because when you go down,

59:17.553 --> 59:20.456
you feel like you take
everybody else down too.

59:25.361 --> 59:27.096
Please tell me
that you're not pinning

59:27.229 --> 59:30.032
your entire future on this.

59:30.166 --> 59:33.703
Especially after what you said
to Banks. I don't--

59:36.505 --> 59:39.408
I don't really know
that you have much of a chance.

59:39.542 --> 59:41.411
But I still have one, right?

59:42.845 --> 59:45.648
Uh, I--

59:42.845 --> 59:45.648
A chance.

59:45.782 --> 59:47.717
It's not up to me, I told you.

59:48.784 --> 59:50.320
Not entirely.

59:54.890 --> 59:57.159
You still have that hair clip
that I got you

59:57.293 --> 59:58.494
for your birthday?

59:57.293 --> 59:58.494
[LAUGHS]

59:58.627 --> 1:00:00.562
No.

59:58.627 --> 1:00:00.562
[CHUCKLES]

1:00:00.696 --> 1:00:01.864
Why?

1:00:07.336 --> 1:00:10.239
[♪♪♪]

1:00:21.550 --> 1:00:24.286
RYAN:
Well, not how I thought
this night would end, heh.

1:00:24.420 --> 1:00:28.291
Yeah. I didn't think
we'd beat Broadmoor either.

1:00:45.541 --> 1:00:46.776
SCOTT:
Is it too late?

1:00:48.510 --> 1:00:50.312
Too late for what?

1:00:50.446 --> 1:00:51.614
For all of it.

1:00:53.849 --> 1:00:55.852
For you, me.

1:00:57.820 --> 1:01:02.125
My dad, the Knights, Nick.

1:01:03.893 --> 1:01:05.795
That's a lot.

1:01:09.465 --> 1:01:11.200
Do you remember
that Spanish Lit class

1:01:11.334 --> 1:01:13.670
that we took together
during my junior year?

1:01:15.237 --> 1:01:18.107
Um, not really.

1:01:15.237 --> 1:01:18.107
[LAUGHS]

1:01:18.240 --> 1:01:19.708
How could you not?

1:01:19.841 --> 1:01:23.579
We had that extensive analysis
of Don Quixote.

1:01:25.014 --> 1:01:27.049
The windmill guy?

1:01:27.183 --> 1:01:28.851
That's what you got from it?

1:01:28.984 --> 1:01:30.586
You wrote both our papers.

1:01:30.720 --> 1:01:32.854
That is true. I did.

1:01:32.988 --> 1:01:34.691
Oh, you were such a jock.

1:01:36.526 --> 1:01:39.062
Well, he said something like:

1:01:39.195 --> 1:01:44.033
"Take my advice
and live for a long, long time.

1:01:44.167 --> 1:01:47.002
Because the maddest thing
a man can do

1:01:47.136 --> 1:01:49.038
is to let himself die."

1:01:51.006 --> 1:01:52.208
So...

1:01:54.410 --> 1:01:57.079
don't die.

1:01:57.213 --> 1:01:58.548
[LAUGHS]

1:02:00.049 --> 1:02:01.451
I guess.

1:02:11.293 --> 1:02:14.664
[CELL PHONE CHIMING]

1:02:19.368 --> 1:02:22.304
Oh, no, that's impossible.

1:02:19.368 --> 1:02:22.304
[SIGHS]

1:02:22.438 --> 1:02:25.108
What time is it?

1:02:22.438 --> 1:02:25.108
Oh, it's time to go.

1:02:26.375 --> 1:02:28.210
What's the matter?

1:02:28.344 --> 1:02:31.079
RYAN:
The press ran photos
of us together last night.

1:02:31.213 --> 1:02:33.615
Um, you afraid
the other players will think

1:02:33.749 --> 1:02:37.419
that I have an unfair advantage?

1:02:33.749 --> 1:02:37.419
Oh, it's not that simple.

1:02:37.553 --> 1:02:40.256
You want me to go?

1:02:37.553 --> 1:02:40.256
[PHONE BUZZING, CHIMING]

1:02:40.389 --> 1:02:41.457
Okay.

1:02:42.725 --> 1:02:44.059
I'm sorry. I just...

1:02:44.193 --> 1:02:45.627
Ryan, it's gonna be okay.

1:02:45.761 --> 1:02:46.929
I don't think it is.

1:02:47.062 --> 1:02:48.296
I don't know anything

1:02:48.430 --> 1:02:50.399
about anything right now,

1:02:50.533 --> 1:02:52.968
but I just know
that my father trusted me

1:02:53.102 --> 1:02:55.138
and I cannot mess this up.

1:02:56.773 --> 1:02:59.475
Ryan...

1:02:56.773 --> 1:02:59.475
I'm sorry about everything.

1:03:02.210 --> 1:03:03.646
What's the matter?

1:03:04.980 --> 1:03:06.749
You made it
into the final round.

1:03:09.051 --> 1:03:11.487
[ENGINE STARTS]

1:03:11.620 --> 1:03:13.322
Great.

1:03:13.455 --> 1:03:16.392
[♪♪♪]

1:03:36.578 --> 1:03:39.748
KRISTINA [ON TV]:
And then there were three.
The competition is fierce

1:03:39.882 --> 1:03:42.017
for the final two spots
on the Knights roster.

1:03:42.151 --> 1:03:44.753
It's down to Air Force veteran
Darryl Coates,

1:03:44.887 --> 1:03:47.523
fireman Clint Dawson,
and most surprising,

1:03:47.656 --> 1:03:50.259
middle-aged Scott Beck,
a former NBA hopeful

1:03:50.392 --> 1:03:53.362
who disappeared from the
limelight almost 20 years ago.

1:03:53.495 --> 1:03:55.497
It makes you wonder
what they're thinking.

1:03:55.631 --> 1:03:58.067
But we'll continue to cover
every step of this story

1:03:58.200 --> 1:03:59.302
as it develops.

1:04:00.436 --> 1:04:02.004
NICK:
Welcome to the FCA.

1:04:02.137 --> 1:04:04.640
We are the Fellowship
of Christian Athletes.

1:04:04.773 --> 1:04:06.875
But you don't have
to be either to check us out.

1:04:07.009 --> 1:04:08.878
In fact, we're made up
of a lot of folks

1:04:09.011 --> 1:04:10.512
from a lot of different places.

1:04:10.646 --> 1:04:13.715
And you might be the folks now
that wanna join us too.

1:04:13.849 --> 1:04:15.384
[CROWD CHEERS]

1:04:16.819 --> 1:04:18.521
The man of the hour, everyone.

1:04:20.623 --> 1:04:21.557
I'm sorry I'm late.

1:04:23.358 --> 1:04:24.627
This is for you.

1:04:26.128 --> 1:04:28.430
Come on, guys.

1:04:28.563 --> 1:04:31.433
Don't look at me.
I had nothing to do with it.

1:04:31.566 --> 1:04:34.503
We thought you would need it,
since you're in the final round.

1:04:34.637 --> 1:04:35.905
Oh, come on.

1:04:37.239 --> 1:04:38.607
This is too much.

1:04:38.741 --> 1:04:41.043
We all chipped in, Mr. Scott.

1:04:41.177 --> 1:04:44.046
Yeah, but I already have
a pair of shoes.

1:04:44.180 --> 1:04:47.016
Yeah, but you can't wear
those janked-up beaters on TV.

1:04:47.149 --> 1:04:49.518
You gotta represent.

1:04:47.149 --> 1:04:49.518
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

1:04:49.652 --> 1:04:51.854
These are nice, guys.
Thank you very much.

1:04:53.155 --> 1:04:54.823
Guys, let me ask you a question.

1:04:54.956 --> 1:04:58.461
How many here
have dreams for the future?

1:04:58.594 --> 1:05:00.896
Yeah, Darcey.

1:04:58.594 --> 1:05:00.896
I wanna be

1:05:01.030 --> 1:05:03.399
the first female astronaut
on the moon.

1:05:04.500 --> 1:05:07.736
That's great. Anyone else?

1:05:07.870 --> 1:05:09.805
FBI, counterintelligence.

1:05:10.906 --> 1:05:12.575
I wanna play in the NBA.

1:05:14.043 --> 1:05:15.411
NICK:
That's good, Murph.

1:05:16.878 --> 1:05:19.515
Let me ask you another question.

1:05:19.649 --> 1:05:21.850
How many of you feel,
as Christians,

1:05:21.984 --> 1:05:24.420
that your life
is immune to failure?

1:05:26.489 --> 1:05:29.157
Like this string right here...

1:05:29.291 --> 1:05:31.760
do you ever think
that your path to success

1:05:31.894 --> 1:05:33.662
is just a straight line that,

1:05:33.795 --> 1:05:37.966
with enough time
and enough prayer,

1:05:38.099 --> 1:05:42.238
eventually you'll rise
to accomplish fulfillment?

1:05:45.774 --> 1:05:48.210
Hey, Murph, would you tie
some knots onto this?

1:05:51.914 --> 1:05:55.317
You know, I feel that
sometimes Christians believe

1:05:55.450 --> 1:05:57.086
that they have a leg up in life.

1:05:58.454 --> 1:06:01.290
I think some of you feel
the same way.

1:06:01.423 --> 1:06:05.160
You know, you've been Psalm 37:4
for so long, right?

1:06:05.294 --> 1:06:07.029
You know,
the desires of your hearts,

1:06:07.163 --> 1:06:08.597
the desires of your hearts...

1:06:08.731 --> 1:06:10.265
And yet now
you've come to a place

1:06:10.399 --> 1:06:12.634
where you actually believe
that's a promise.

1:06:12.768 --> 1:06:16.304
Would you put that on the floor,
Murph?

1:06:16.438 --> 1:06:18.507
That's okay. Go on.

1:06:18.640 --> 1:06:20.442
Stomp on it.

1:06:20.576 --> 1:06:22.010
Go on. Stomp.

1:06:22.144 --> 1:06:23.445
Harder. Stomp!

1:06:23.579 --> 1:06:25.414
Like, you know,
Jesus is supposed to be

1:06:25.547 --> 1:06:27.115
at our beck and call, isn't he?

1:06:27.249 --> 1:06:29.351
I mean, he's that genie
in a bottle.

1:06:29.485 --> 1:06:31.787
Whatever we ask,
he's gonna grant us every wish.

1:06:31.920 --> 1:06:34.689
Don't stop, Murphy.
Stomp on it. Flatten it out.

1:06:34.823 --> 1:06:36.659
Hard! Come on.
Drag it through the mud.

1:06:36.792 --> 1:06:39.628
Flatten it out. Hard, Murphy!
Stop.

1:06:41.630 --> 1:06:42.798
Pick it up.

1:06:45.200 --> 1:06:46.369
Look at it.

1:06:47.469 --> 1:06:48.771
Pass it down.

1:06:51.273 --> 1:06:55.811
What if that string was told
its entire life

1:06:55.944 --> 1:06:57.179
that it was worthless

1:06:57.312 --> 1:06:59.715
or that it would
never amount to anything?

1:07:01.249 --> 1:07:02.351
What if it was told

1:07:02.484 --> 1:07:04.653
that it just wasn't
pretty enough?

1:07:04.786 --> 1:07:06.988
Or smart enough?

1:07:07.122 --> 1:07:08.391
Or too old?

1:07:09.491 --> 1:07:11.027
Too fat?

1:07:12.528 --> 1:07:14.563
Oh, yeah.

1:07:14.696 --> 1:07:17.900
Life is gonna give you plenty
of reasons to feel discouraged.

1:07:18.033 --> 1:07:21.637
All right? Plenty of reasons
to lose your faith.

1:07:21.771 --> 1:07:23.805
Especially when
it looks like that.

1:07:23.939 --> 1:07:26.842
Knotted up in a tangled mess.

1:07:26.975 --> 1:07:29.178
Darcey, would you
give that to me?

1:07:31.346 --> 1:07:32.515
Thank you.

1:07:38.253 --> 1:07:42.858
God never promised us
a life free from trouble.

1:07:44.559 --> 1:07:46.262
Or free from failure.

1:07:49.365 --> 1:07:55.404
In fact, Job 14:1 says that
"Mortals born of women...

1:07:55.537 --> 1:07:59.275
few are their days,
and full of trouble."

1:08:01.143 --> 1:08:03.446
That's not just
for non-believers.

1:08:07.048 --> 1:08:08.784
That's for all of us.

1:08:12.954 --> 1:08:15.156
So the question isn't

1:08:15.290 --> 1:08:18.594
if you're gonna have
to ever face failure.

1:08:22.097 --> 1:08:23.632
The question is when.

1:08:25.834 --> 1:08:28.737
[♪♪♪]

1:08:33.909 --> 1:08:35.310
We'd have to.

1:08:33.909 --> 1:08:35.310
Mm, yeah.

1:08:35.443 --> 1:08:37.178
While he don't stop us--

1:08:35.443 --> 1:08:37.178
Hey.

1:08:37.312 --> 1:08:39.448
Is something wrong
with your phone?

1:08:47.589 --> 1:08:50.526
Is there something
I can do for you, Ms. Aikens?

1:08:50.659 --> 1:08:52.528
You know I can have you fired,
right?

1:08:55.096 --> 1:08:56.132
Or I could resign.

1:08:57.432 --> 1:08:58.700
Either way,

1:08:58.833 --> 1:09:01.603
the board's gonna
run you out on a rail.

1:09:01.736 --> 1:09:04.139
Scott Beck was passed
through to the final round

1:09:04.272 --> 1:09:06.908
with no intention
of signing him.

1:09:07.042 --> 1:09:07.976
That's a fact.

1:09:08.109 --> 1:09:10.846
Why? Why would you do that?

1:09:10.979 --> 1:09:12.514
I didn't.

1:09:12.647 --> 1:09:13.816
I did.

1:09:18.253 --> 1:09:21.290
Scott Beck's too valuable
to this franchise.

1:09:21.423 --> 1:09:23.492
Can't afford to let him go now.

1:09:23.625 --> 1:09:27.162
Everybody loves
a comeback story.

1:09:27.295 --> 1:09:32.934
Add a little bit of "rich girl,
poor guy" topspin to it,

1:09:33.068 --> 1:09:35.036
that's the stuff
that dreams are made of.

1:09:35.170 --> 1:09:38.240
And, baby, dreams sell.

1:09:38.373 --> 1:09:42.510
Look, tens of millions
of dollars in free publicity.

1:09:42.644 --> 1:09:45.881
The pre-season ticket sales,
historic high.

1:09:46.014 --> 1:09:48.216
Dozen bids on my desk right now

1:09:48.350 --> 1:09:51.320
for the streaming rights
to the last round,

1:09:51.453 --> 1:09:55.390
and a larger share of the female
demographic than ever before.

1:09:55.524 --> 1:09:57.159
I mean, you wanted to generate

1:09:57.292 --> 1:09:59.694
some publicity
for your franchise,

1:09:59.828 --> 1:10:00.863
you did it.

1:10:00.996 --> 1:10:02.731
You should be proud.

1:10:02.865 --> 1:10:05.667
No, I'm-- I'm not proud.

1:10:05.800 --> 1:10:07.836
No, not this way.
Come on, coach.

1:10:09.505 --> 1:10:11.140
I told you from the start...

1:10:12.807 --> 1:10:15.411
I wanted no part of this.

1:10:12.807 --> 1:10:15.411
[SIGHS]

1:10:17.112 --> 1:10:18.914
You let me know
when you're ready for me

1:10:19.048 --> 1:10:20.749
to coach your basketball team.

1:10:23.852 --> 1:10:27.323
That's all right. Let him go.
He'll get over it.

1:10:29.225 --> 1:10:31.659
Scott deserves
to know the truth.

1:10:31.793 --> 1:10:33.429
No. No, he doesn't. No.

1:10:33.562 --> 1:10:35.931
You cannot risk
that he'll run to the press.

1:10:36.065 --> 1:10:37.999
It'll destroy everything
we built so far.

1:10:38.132 --> 1:10:43.105
The franchise... Your franchise
will not survive it.

1:10:44.406 --> 1:10:46.275
This is gonna devastate him.

1:10:48.176 --> 1:10:49.645
Only if you tell him.

1:10:52.848 --> 1:10:55.717
You think I should cut my hair?

1:10:55.851 --> 1:10:58.320
What are you asking me for?

1:10:55.851 --> 1:10:58.320
Hmm.

1:10:59.855 --> 1:11:03.559
Hey, you, uh...
You like this shaving cream?

1:11:05.227 --> 1:11:07.462
What's going on with you, man?

1:11:07.595 --> 1:11:09.265
I don't know. I just--
I, uh--

1:11:09.398 --> 1:11:12.101
I feel like I got a shot
at getting my life back.

1:11:12.234 --> 1:11:14.269
Scott, you've always had
your life.

1:11:14.403 --> 1:11:16.371
You're just not doing anything
with it.

1:11:16.505 --> 1:11:19.741
Yeah, well,
I owe a lot of it to you.

1:11:19.875 --> 1:11:21.243
Yeah, well-- Wait.

1:11:22.844 --> 1:11:24.046
For real?

1:11:25.947 --> 1:11:27.549
Yeah.

1:11:27.682 --> 1:11:29.952
You telling me
I ministered to you?

1:11:30.085 --> 1:11:31.654
That's awesome.

1:11:34.522 --> 1:11:36.057
Live for God

1:11:36.191 --> 1:11:38.260
and you'll never
have a reason to quit.

1:11:38.393 --> 1:11:40.796
All right, just, you know,
tone down the "pastor speak."

1:11:40.929 --> 1:11:42.965
You're starting
to sound like a fortune cookie.

1:11:43.098 --> 1:11:45.534
Yeah, you're right.

1:11:43.098 --> 1:11:45.534
I'll see you later.

1:11:56.811 --> 1:11:58.880
Your daddy sat right there

1:11:59.013 --> 1:12:02.318
and worried about the same thing
you are right now.

1:12:03.786 --> 1:12:07.022
What to do about Scott Beck.

1:12:10.792 --> 1:12:15.497
I put him out of my mind
and moved on with my life.

1:12:15.630 --> 1:12:16.932
And then...

1:12:21.170 --> 1:12:25.440
[VOICE BREAKS]
Now that he's back, I'm just--
I'm afraid to lose him again.

1:12:25.573 --> 1:12:28.944
Well, that's his choice,
and you have to let him make it.

1:12:30.112 --> 1:12:32.147
If you're not honest with him,

1:12:32.281 --> 1:12:35.117
you take away his right
to fight for you.

1:12:35.250 --> 1:12:38.019
Whatever happens,
for the rest of your life,

1:12:38.153 --> 1:12:39.988
you'll know who he really is.

1:12:40.121 --> 1:12:42.624
I don't...
I don't know, Ruby.

1:12:42.757 --> 1:12:48.529
Everybody says that Scott just
used me to get into the NBA.

1:12:48.663 --> 1:12:50.365
You don't believe that.

1:12:50.499 --> 1:12:56.171
Scott grew up blue collar
in a working-class family.

1:12:56.304 --> 1:13:00.241
They didn't have two nickels
to rub together.

1:13:00.375 --> 1:13:02.244
How do you think that feels

1:13:02.377 --> 1:13:07.048
when the girl he loves
was born with a silver spoon?

1:13:07.182 --> 1:13:09.351
I always just tried
to assure him

1:13:09.485 --> 1:13:11.553
that that was never
gonna be a thing.

1:13:11.687 --> 1:13:14.056
Whose voice
do you think was the loudest?

1:13:14.189 --> 1:13:16.592
Yours or the one inside his head

1:13:16.725 --> 1:13:19.995
that told him he'd never
be good enough for you?

1:13:20.129 --> 1:13:25.167
An NBA contract
put you on equal ground.

1:13:25.300 --> 1:13:28.836
He didn't use you
to get to the NBA.

1:13:28.970 --> 1:13:31.706
Darling, don't you see?

1:13:31.840 --> 1:13:34.610
He used the NBA to get you.

1:13:36.044 --> 1:13:38.947
[♪♪♪]

1:13:42.584 --> 1:13:43.585
[DOG WHIMPERS]

1:13:49.124 --> 1:13:51.393
No more people food for you.

1:13:51.526 --> 1:13:53.929
Your stuff is in the bowl
on the floor.

1:14:02.938 --> 1:14:04.605
Looks like I got a date, heh.

1:14:04.739 --> 1:14:05.808
[BARKS]

1:14:08.810 --> 1:14:10.779
We'll discuss your diet later.

1:14:17.318 --> 1:14:18.754
SCOTT:
All right, guys.

1:14:20.188 --> 1:14:21.156
That.

1:14:21.289 --> 1:14:24.459
Thank you, guys.
I appreciate this.

1:14:24.592 --> 1:14:27.595
Look at that. All right,
you guys, nothing is impossible.

1:14:27.729 --> 1:14:29.798
I appreciate you guys.
Thank you again.

1:14:31.633 --> 1:14:33.501
Hey, gorgeous.

1:14:33.635 --> 1:14:35.169
More paperwork for me to sign?

1:14:35.303 --> 1:14:36.571
Uh, no.

1:14:36.704 --> 1:14:37.973
[CLEARS THROAT]

1:14:36.704 --> 1:14:37.973
Ah.

1:14:39.741 --> 1:14:42.110
Remember this big guy?

1:14:39.741 --> 1:14:42.110
Oh, wow.

1:14:42.243 --> 1:14:44.178
One we'd order
after winning a game.

1:14:44.312 --> 1:14:46.648
Yeah.

1:14:44.312 --> 1:14:46.648
Thank you, Kim.

1:14:46.781 --> 1:14:49.685
[EXHALES SHARPLY] So, Scott...

1:14:46.781 --> 1:14:49.685
Look, I know.

1:14:49.818 --> 1:14:53.521
I'm sorry about last night.
I wasn't thinking.

1:14:53.655 --> 1:14:57.159
For once,
it felt good not to...

1:14:57.292 --> 1:15:00.295
[SIGHS]
Not to think, that is.

1:15:00.428 --> 1:15:04.699
Look, Ry, I, uh-- I'm not
really any good at this.

1:15:04.833 --> 1:15:08.170
But what I'm trying to say is--

1:15:04.833 --> 1:15:08.170
They're not gonna let you play.

1:15:10.771 --> 1:15:12.407
What do you mean?

1:15:12.540 --> 1:15:14.576
I was trying to do
something meaningful.

1:15:14.709 --> 1:15:16.711
You have to believe that.

1:15:16.844 --> 1:15:21.549
But for Archie, I guess
it was just all for the cameras.

1:15:21.683 --> 1:15:24.720
That's it? I'm done?
I'm just--? I'm out?

1:15:26.287 --> 1:15:27.656
I'm sorry.

1:15:30.625 --> 1:15:32.560
No, look, you know what?
It's...

1:15:32.694 --> 1:15:35.363
Scott, listen.

1:15:32.694 --> 1:15:35.363
I know. It's all good.

1:15:35.497 --> 1:15:37.699
Can we talk about it?

1:15:35.497 --> 1:15:37.699
It's good.

1:15:37.832 --> 1:15:40.736
[♪♪♪]

1:15:45.340 --> 1:15:47.376
Scott, wait. Talk to me.

1:15:49.544 --> 1:15:51.780
I might have even played along

1:15:51.913 --> 1:15:53.248
if you would've
let me in on it.

1:15:53.382 --> 1:15:54.783
That's not how it happened,
I swear.

1:15:54.916 --> 1:15:56.518
You used me, Ry!

1:15:58.553 --> 1:16:00.955
You knew that
I never stopped loving you.

1:16:01.089 --> 1:16:04.058
You knew that I'd spend
the rest of my life

1:16:04.192 --> 1:16:05.726
looking for your forgiveness.

1:16:05.860 --> 1:16:07.629
And you let me believe...

1:16:11.066 --> 1:16:12.801
that I still had a chance.

1:16:14.268 --> 1:16:16.071
I'm just like that guy
chasing windmills.

1:16:43.064 --> 1:16:45.968
[♪♪♪]

1:17:12.594 --> 1:17:14.796
[♪♪♪]

1:17:14.929 --> 1:17:16.932
[CHEERLEADERS YELL
INDISTINCTLY]

1:17:17.065 --> 1:17:19.501
[CROWD CHEERING, WHISTLING]

1:17:24.439 --> 1:17:26.808
MAN 1:
The entire season is hanging
in the balance.

1:17:26.942 --> 1:17:29.144
Senior Scott Beck, with
only seconds on the clock...

1:17:29.277 --> 1:17:30.612
MAN 2:
He shoots
from deep in the paint.

1:17:30.745 --> 1:17:32.480
It's a goal!
Texas Christian wins!

1:17:32.613 --> 1:17:35.584
Are you kidding me?

1:17:32.613 --> 1:17:35.584
MAN 1: Beck scores again!

1:17:35.717 --> 1:17:37.919
MAN 2:
That's the most incredible shot
I've ever seen.

1:17:38.052 --> 1:17:39.988
MAN 1:
That sends Texas Christian
to the state finals.

1:17:40.122 --> 1:17:42.190
MAN 3:
Last-minute save by Scott Beck.

1:17:42.323 --> 1:17:43.825
MAN 1:
Amazing!

1:17:50.132 --> 1:17:52.000
LAWRENCE:
A lot of times
we go through life

1:17:52.133 --> 1:17:56.505
and go through challenges, and
we want to just stop and quit.

1:17:58.005 --> 1:18:00.342
What if the Lord would
have quit

1:18:00.475 --> 1:18:02.244
up on that cross?

1:18:02.377 --> 1:18:05.313
[♪♪♪]

1:18:38.946 --> 1:18:40.515
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

1:18:42.317 --> 1:18:44.051
Hello?

1:18:42.317 --> 1:18:44.051
RYAN [OVER SPEAKER]: Hi, Nick.

1:18:44.185 --> 1:18:46.821
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Who's this?

1:18:46.955 --> 1:18:48.323
It's Ryan.

1:19:05.106 --> 1:19:06.975
[PANTING]

1:19:11.379 --> 1:19:12.914
Why, God?

1:19:14.949 --> 1:19:16.618
Why did you make me...

1:19:18.586 --> 1:19:20.922
think that I could
get it all back...

1:19:23.091 --> 1:19:25.660
just so you could take it away
from me again?

1:19:28.729 --> 1:19:30.599
Are you trying to punish me?

1:19:32.434 --> 1:19:34.068
Are you trying
to show me something?

1:19:34.201 --> 1:19:36.638
Just show me. Show me, what?

1:19:39.074 --> 1:19:40.442
Just show me.

1:19:48.182 --> 1:19:49.284
Scott.

1:19:51.052 --> 1:19:52.587
What are you doing here?

1:19:56.624 --> 1:19:58.093
Let's go home, buddy.

1:20:24.819 --> 1:20:27.656
Look, if you need anything...

1:20:29.023 --> 1:20:31.493
Maybe it's not that bad,
you know?

1:20:36.597 --> 1:20:37.632
Scott.

1:20:54.482 --> 1:20:55.784
Pastor Lawrence...

1:20:58.652 --> 1:21:00.055
I need your help.

1:21:04.692 --> 1:21:06.428
Yesterday he was thanking me.

1:21:08.029 --> 1:21:09.931
Now today I think
he's blaming me.

1:21:11.733 --> 1:21:13.368
You didn't do anything wrong.

1:21:15.136 --> 1:21:16.871
You see, the problem is,

1:21:17.004 --> 1:21:19.874
Scott is missing
the bigger picture.

1:21:20.007 --> 1:21:22.076
God's picture.

1:21:22.209 --> 1:21:25.680
If he's ready to talk to me,
I think I can help him.

1:21:25.813 --> 1:21:29.117
But, Nick, you can't force him.

1:21:31.185 --> 1:21:33.021
Yeah, I know.

1:21:33.154 --> 1:21:34.989
Why are you forcing me
to do this?

1:21:35.123 --> 1:21:36.757
I'm not forcing you
to do anything.

1:21:36.891 --> 1:21:39.560
Pastor Lawrence wants
to talk to you.

1:21:39.693 --> 1:21:41.429
LAWRENCE:
Let's go. Keep it crisp.

1:21:42.497 --> 1:21:43.598
D up.

1:21:43.731 --> 1:21:45.066
[CLAPS HANDS]

1:21:45.199 --> 1:21:46.601
That's it.

1:21:49.571 --> 1:21:51.606
NICK:
Hey, Pastor Lawrence.

1:21:51.739 --> 1:21:54.075
Hey, Scott, come on over.

1:21:58.913 --> 1:22:00.215
LAWRENCE:
Way to go.

1:22:09.024 --> 1:22:10.325
Hey, Scott.

1:22:09.024 --> 1:22:10.325
Hey.

1:22:12.193 --> 1:22:14.161
Spinal cord injuries,
spina bifida,

1:22:14.295 --> 1:22:16.231
amputations,
many are wounded vets.

1:22:17.598 --> 1:22:19.634
But out there,
none of it matters.

1:22:19.767 --> 1:22:22.436
They refuse to let
any of it define them.

1:22:22.570 --> 1:22:24.172
They don't even
talk about handicaps

1:22:24.305 --> 1:22:25.740
and disabilities out there.

1:22:25.873 --> 1:22:27.008
Only opportunity.

1:22:28.209 --> 1:22:29.844
Body of Christ in action.

1:22:31.913 --> 1:22:35.583
Yes, we live in
a broken, unfair world.

1:22:35.717 --> 1:22:37.752
But God is faithful.

1:22:39.454 --> 1:22:41.822
You might think you finished.
Done.

1:22:41.956 --> 1:22:44.092
But God is not done with you.

1:22:45.960 --> 1:22:49.496
He's still working in you
and through you.

1:22:49.630 --> 1:22:51.166
But you have to be available.

1:22:52.567 --> 1:22:54.936
You're still living, Scott.

1:22:55.069 --> 1:22:56.271
Still breathing.

1:22:57.571 --> 1:22:59.808
Where there's life,
there's hope.

1:23:01.408 --> 1:23:03.645
It all just seems so impossible.

1:23:05.079 --> 1:23:06.914
[CHUCKLES]

1:23:07.048 --> 1:23:11.686
You know, when God is going
to do something wonderful,

1:23:11.819 --> 1:23:16.357
it seems he always starts
with a hardship.

1:23:16.490 --> 1:23:19.394
But when God is going to do
something amazing...

1:23:20.962 --> 1:23:22.731
he starts with the impossible.

1:23:25.933 --> 1:23:28.303
What do you say we go meet them?
They'd love that.

1:23:28.436 --> 1:23:30.338
Not today.

1:23:28.436 --> 1:23:30.338
No, you're meeting them.

1:23:30.472 --> 1:23:31.805
[BLOWS]

1:23:31.939 --> 1:23:33.174
Hey, guys. Scott Beck is here.

1:23:33.307 --> 1:23:35.376
Come on, gather around
and meet him.

1:23:35.510 --> 1:23:38.213
Hey. Hey, guys. How you doing?

1:23:38.346 --> 1:23:40.315
Good to meet you.
I'm a really big fan.

1:23:41.649 --> 1:23:42.717
Real cool to meet you.

1:23:42.850 --> 1:23:44.552
Nice to meet you too.

1:23:44.686 --> 1:23:45.653
Gunner.

1:23:45.786 --> 1:23:47.555
Nice to meet you.

1:23:47.688 --> 1:23:50.291
LAWRENCE:
Heavenly Father, we come to you

1:23:50.425 --> 1:23:53.027
with our hearts bowed, Father,
we ask that you would lift up

1:23:53.161 --> 1:23:55.963
our brother Scott to you
and that you would bless him.

1:23:56.096 --> 1:23:59.300
Father, we ask that you would
give us strength and endurance.

1:23:59.433 --> 1:24:03.337
No matter what the score,
no matter what the odds.

1:24:03.471 --> 1:24:08.043
We ask you these things in
the mighty name of Jesus. Amen.

1:24:20.555 --> 1:24:21.856
[SIGHS]

1:24:46.347 --> 1:24:48.349
What are you doing?

1:24:48.482 --> 1:24:50.918
Come on, get dressed.
I'm taking you to the doctor.

1:24:51.052 --> 1:24:53.688
I told you, there's no point.

1:24:53.821 --> 1:24:55.856
Well, you're alive, aren't you?

1:24:55.990 --> 1:24:58.626
Then you might as well stay
that way for as long as you can.

1:24:58.760 --> 1:25:00.595
Come on, let's go, Pop.

1:25:00.728 --> 1:25:02.764
You don't understand.

1:25:08.069 --> 1:25:10.605
You don't think
that I understand, Pop?

1:25:13.374 --> 1:25:15.410
I understand
more than you think.

1:25:19.313 --> 1:25:22.417
That's why we're gonna get you
into the program.

1:25:22.550 --> 1:25:25.120
We'll go on back to church,
we're gonna do...

1:25:26.287 --> 1:25:27.922
whatever it takes.

1:25:29.724 --> 1:25:31.826
But you have to leave
this pain behind you.

1:25:34.496 --> 1:25:36.531
You don't think
that I miss her too?

1:25:38.332 --> 1:25:41.536
You don't think that
I carry that around with me?

1:25:44.071 --> 1:25:46.608
We're doing okay,
aren't we, Scott?

1:25:48.543 --> 1:25:49.777
No, Pop.

1:25:52.647 --> 1:25:54.282
But we will.

1:26:01.656 --> 1:26:02.991
We will.

1:26:07.428 --> 1:26:09.329
This is it,
Silver Knights fans.

1:26:09.463 --> 1:26:10.998
Today is the final day

1:26:11.131 --> 1:26:13.634
of owner Ryan Aikens'
ambitious experiment.

1:26:13.767 --> 1:26:15.369
And our very own Kristina Walsh

1:26:15.503 --> 1:26:17.905
is on location
just outside the arena.

1:26:18.039 --> 1:26:21.208
People are gathered today
and the excitement is palpable.

1:26:21.342 --> 1:26:23.644
You would think
that this was a playoff game.

1:26:23.778 --> 1:26:26.014
[ALL CHEERING]

1:26:37.458 --> 1:26:39.360
Scott's not showing up, is he?

1:26:39.494 --> 1:26:41.563
Mm, doubtful.

1:26:44.498 --> 1:26:46.568
You told him, didn't you?

1:26:48.602 --> 1:26:51.572
Then what am I supposed
to tell the press?

1:26:51.705 --> 1:26:53.674
Oh, well,
he just didn't show up.

1:26:53.807 --> 1:26:55.376
RYAN:
Scott made his decision,

1:26:55.509 --> 1:26:57.578
and we have to move forward
without him.

1:26:57.712 --> 1:27:00.215
Oh, without him. Oh, okay.

1:27:03.717 --> 1:27:05.386
Absolutely great.

1:27:08.689 --> 1:27:09.824
[POPPING LIPS]

1:27:11.392 --> 1:27:14.829
Wha--? Hey.
Where you going now?

1:27:14.962 --> 1:27:17.198
[♪♪♪]

1:27:36.784 --> 1:27:40.421
You know they don't allow people
to be barefoot on the court.

1:27:41.589 --> 1:27:43.224
I own this court.

1:27:44.792 --> 1:27:45.994
Good point.

1:27:49.030 --> 1:27:50.765
Why are you here, Scott?

1:27:53.267 --> 1:27:55.703
You keep asking me that.

1:27:55.836 --> 1:27:59.874
I guess I wanna do more
with my life than just give up.

1:28:00.007 --> 1:28:02.477
I don't wanna be Scott
"What a Shame" Beck anymore.

1:28:03.611 --> 1:28:05.379
It was shame that...

1:28:05.513 --> 1:28:07.749
kept me from seeing
God's purpose for me.

1:28:09.083 --> 1:28:10.485
Kept me from you, Ry.

1:28:11.686 --> 1:28:13.821
You deserved better than that.

1:28:13.954 --> 1:28:15.123
We both did.

1:28:16.290 --> 1:28:17.592
I'm sorry.

1:28:27.902 --> 1:28:29.270
You got an H.

1:28:30.972 --> 1:28:34.341
Look, I didn't use you.

1:28:34.475 --> 1:28:36.677
Maybe there was a part of me

1:28:36.811 --> 1:28:39.047
that saw
what was going on, but...

1:28:40.347 --> 1:28:42.483
another part
that was just afraid

1:28:42.616 --> 1:28:44.819
to lose you again.

1:28:44.952 --> 1:28:46.720
It's okay.

1:28:46.853 --> 1:28:48.655
As Nick would say,

1:28:48.789 --> 1:28:51.125
I'm exactly
where God wants me to be.

1:28:57.264 --> 1:29:01.201
You know that, uh, saying
you were asking me about?

1:29:01.335 --> 1:29:03.671
About the twists
and the turns of life.

1:29:05.640 --> 1:29:06.974
I mean, I suppose in the end

1:29:07.107 --> 1:29:09.677
it could be called fate,
but to me,

1:29:09.811 --> 1:29:11.612
it's more a matter of faith.

1:29:14.782 --> 1:29:15.983
What's the score?

1:29:17.351 --> 1:29:18.720
You tell me.

1:29:23.957 --> 1:29:25.092
Nice shot.

1:29:25.225 --> 1:29:27.061
[CROWD CHEERING]

1:29:27.194 --> 1:29:29.563
Looks like they're getting ready
to start without me.

1:29:29.697 --> 1:29:32.032
The tryouts?

1:29:32.166 --> 1:29:33.101
But why?

1:29:35.536 --> 1:29:39.106
At first, I wanted everybody
to see me win.

1:29:39.239 --> 1:29:41.375
But now I think
there's more people out there

1:29:41.509 --> 1:29:43.277
that need to see me not lose.

1:29:45.813 --> 1:29:47.849
What's the endgame?

1:29:47.982 --> 1:29:50.384
We don't always get to see
the finish line, Ry.

1:29:50.518 --> 1:29:52.453
You know that.

1:29:52.586 --> 1:29:55.523
But he guides us
one step at a time.

1:29:58.392 --> 1:30:01.229
And it'll make a great story
for our kids one day.

1:30:05.299 --> 1:30:08.769
Oh, you do realize that I just
asked you to marry me, right?

1:30:08.902 --> 1:30:10.838
You don't have to decide now.
Just, you know...

1:30:12.306 --> 1:30:13.674
Think about it.

1:30:21.582 --> 1:30:23.417
Ah, I got it.

1:30:23.551 --> 1:30:25.119
The ball's in my court?

1:30:26.420 --> 1:30:27.889
That's a good one.

1:30:35.629 --> 1:30:37.898
ANNOUNCER:
The stands of this tiny
practice gym are filled

1:30:38.031 --> 1:30:39.567
with fans, family and friends.

1:30:39.700 --> 1:30:41.068
However, I'm looking around,

1:30:41.201 --> 1:30:43.304
Scott Beck is nowhere
to be seen.

1:30:45.305 --> 1:30:48.242
[CROWD CHEERING, APPLAUDING]

1:31:01.588 --> 1:31:04.392
Now that we're all here,
let's get the show started.

1:31:04.525 --> 1:31:06.059
How'd you get him to come?

1:31:06.193 --> 1:31:07.995
Oh, I couldn't stop him.

1:31:10.030 --> 1:31:11.599
Scrimmages.

1:31:11.732 --> 1:31:14.968
Three-on-three. This side,
black. This side, white.

1:31:15.102 --> 1:31:18.171
You have three minutes
to get to know your team.

1:31:18.305 --> 1:31:19.774
Then we play ball.

1:31:25.646 --> 1:31:27.381
Hey, Hal.

1:31:27.515 --> 1:31:29.050
Come sit with us.

1:31:34.755 --> 1:31:35.989
Good to see you.

1:31:36.123 --> 1:31:39.526
Listen, this is yours to lose.

1:31:39.660 --> 1:31:42.196
Read that contract
that you signed?

1:31:42.329 --> 1:31:43.865
They don't have to hire anyone.

1:31:45.299 --> 1:31:48.970
So just relax. Have fun.
Make it count.

1:31:49.103 --> 1:31:51.338
Yeah, what about you?

1:31:49.103 --> 1:31:51.338
Don't worry about me.

1:31:51.472 --> 1:31:53.374
All right?
Just keep your head in this.

1:31:53.507 --> 1:31:55.476
By this time tomorrow,
you'll be a Knight.

1:31:55.609 --> 1:31:57.410
All right.

1:31:57.544 --> 1:31:59.012
Jeffries, right?

1:31:57.544 --> 1:31:59.012
Yeah.

1:31:59.146 --> 1:32:00.982
I'm a fan.

1:31:59.146 --> 1:32:00.982
Thank you.

1:32:01.115 --> 1:32:03.884
You score 92% of the time
from offensive boards.

1:32:04.018 --> 1:32:05.186
Appreciate that.

1:32:04.018 --> 1:32:05.186
Yeah.

1:32:05.319 --> 1:32:06.787
Blue four.

1:32:06.921 --> 1:32:08.388
All right?
Hang out in the paint.

1:32:08.522 --> 1:32:10.223
And when the time is right,
you'll know what to do.

1:32:10.357 --> 1:32:11.859
Whatever you say, coach.

1:32:13.260 --> 1:32:15.496
Gentlemen, it's an honor.

1:32:15.629 --> 1:32:18.533
[♪♪♪]

1:32:24.504 --> 1:32:27.008
[ALL CHEER]

1:32:44.725 --> 1:32:46.260
Don't you think he should
come out more like that?

1:32:46.393 --> 1:32:47.895
Be more able to work?

1:32:48.028 --> 1:32:49.864
That work?

1:32:48.028 --> 1:32:49.864
Yeah, that's better.

1:33:02.009 --> 1:33:05.079
Your boyfriend's doing
pretty well out there.

1:33:05.212 --> 1:33:07.347
Like a man with nothing to lose.

1:33:07.481 --> 1:33:10.017
Don't you think
we should end this thing?

1:33:10.150 --> 1:33:12.687
Before they start
building statues to the guy.

1:33:16.057 --> 1:33:18.593
I'm about done
with you telling me what to do.

1:33:35.609 --> 1:33:36.811
[BLOWS]

1:33:44.751 --> 1:33:45.953
Scott Beck.

1:33:49.590 --> 1:33:54.595
Every man here ran the suicide
in less than 35 seconds.

1:33:54.728 --> 1:33:59.166
Your best time is 37.5.
Legs are the first to go.

1:33:59.299 --> 1:34:00.701
I'm sorry, son.

